01:59:08,490 --> 01:59:12,715
BBC World Service, it's two o'clock GMT, this is Oliver Conway with the Newsroom.

1382
01:59:13,036 --> 01:59:21,507
The US President Donald Trump is expected to recognise Jerusalem as the capital of Israel later, breaking with the international consensus on the city's status.

1383
01:59:21,858 --> 01:59:25,360
I know there have been a lot of questions surrounding the president's decision on Jerusalem.

1384
01:59:25,820 --> 01:59:27,701
Tomorrow the president will deliver remarks.

1385
01:59:28,281 --> 01:59:30,322
Has the president made up his mind?

1386
01:59:30,382 --> 01:59:33,543
The president is pretty solid in his thinking at this point.

1387
01:59:33,883 --> 01:59:34,944
Also on the newsroom.

1388
01:59:35,224 --> 01:59:36,524
It's a political decision.

1389
01:59:36,645 --> 01:59:37,725
Very bad decision.

1390
01:59:38,065 --> 01:59:39,446
And I disagree.

1391
01:59:40,146 --> 01:59:44,208
This position of the World Olympic Committee and so on.

1392
01:59:44,568 --> 01:59:49,370
There's been a furious reaction in Moscow after Russia was banned from next year's Winter Olympics.

1393
01:59:49,970 --> 01:59:53,852
Tens of thousands of Californians have fled wildfires north of Los Angeles.

1394
01:59:54,352 --> 01:59:58,895
Good friends up the street lost their homes, and I'm just so sad for them.

1395
01:59:59,595 --> 02:00:04,417
And have investigators issued a subpoena for Donald Trump's financial records at Deutsche Bank?

1396
02:00:04,917 --> 02:00:06,118
First, our top stories.

1397
02:00:08,325 --> 02:00:10,026
BBC News with Gareth Barlow.

1398
02:00:10,647 --> 02:00:16,552
Senior US officials say President Trump will recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel later on Wednesday.

1399
02:00:16,572 --> 02:00:23,418
He'll also direct the State Department to start the process of moving the American embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.

1400
02:00:23,959 --> 02:00:26,661
Arab states have warned that the decision could provoke violence.

1401
02:00:27,041 --> 02:00:28,863
From Washington, here's Barbara Pletusher.

1402
02:00:29,323 --> 02:00:33,309
The president is planning to fulfill a campaign promise made to pro-Israel voters.

1403
02:00:33,730 --> 02:00:39,538
But in doing so, he's tackling one of the most sensitive issues in the Israeli-Palestinian conflict, the status of Jerusalem.

1404
02:00:40,399 --> 02:00:43,825
Senior administration officials said he would simply be acknowledging reality,

1405
02:00:44,225 --> 02:00:46,667
that Jerusalem functions as the capital of Israel.

1406
02:00:47,247 --> 02:00:55,794
Congress has called for such a move for 22 years, but previous presidents have been resistant, accepting that Jerusalem's future should be part of a negotiated agreement.

1407
02:00:56,535 --> 02:00:56,955
One U.S.

1408
02:00:56,995 --> 02:01:00,878
official said that delaying the decision had done nothing to advance peace.

1409
02:01:01,519 --> 02:01:05,502
But the U.N., Europe and Arab states have long calculated that it would prevent conflict.

1410
02:01:06,256 --> 02:01:13,583
Russia has reacted furiously to a decision by the International Olympic Committee to ban it from next February's Winter Olympics in South Korea.

1411
02:01:14,104 --> 02:01:20,710
A damning report by the IOC said there had been an unprecedented systematic manipulation of the anti-doping system.

1412
02:01:21,151 --> 02:01:22,972
From Moscow, here's Steve Rosenberg.

1413
02:01:23,553 --> 02:01:28,318
The deputy speaker of Russia's parliament said it was a humiliation and an insult to Russia.

1414
02:01:29,178 --> 02:01:40,809
In a defiant post in social media, the spokeswoman for the Russian Foreign Ministry said Russia would survive this like it survived World War, the collapse of the Soviet Union and Western sanctions.

1415
02:01:41,850 --> 02:01:51,179
Although the Russian team has been banned from competing in South Korea, Russian athletes who can prove they are clean will be permitted to participate under the Olympic flag.

1416
02:01:51,900 --> 02:01:53,642
But will the Kremlin allow them to?

1417
02:01:54,322 --> 02:01:59,589
Vladimir Putin has in the past described such a scenario as a humiliation for his country.

1418
02:02:00,229 --> 02:02:05,576
Tens of thousands of people in Southern California have fled wildfires being driven by high winds.

1419
02:02:05,996 --> 02:02:08,620
James Cook reports from the outskirts of Los Angeles.

1420
02:02:09,075 --> 02:02:21,331
In Ventura County, to the north of Los Angeles, a wildfire which broke out on Monday intensified with terrifying speed, trembling in size in just a few hours, driven by arid and gusty Santa Ana winds.

1421
02:02:21,812 --> 02:02:25,557
Scores of homes were gutted and a mental health hospital was destroyed.

1422
02:02:26,157 --> 02:02:34,221
Here, on the outskirts of Los Angeles, the charred ruins of houses are still smoking, while dark, choking smoke has closed a major moat away.

1423
02:02:34,781 --> 02:02:38,643
Ash is blowing through the air, and there is a firefighting helicopter overhead.

1424
02:02:39,183 --> 02:02:46,567
And with forecasters warning that ferocious winds and low humidity will continue for several days, this could yet get a lot worse.

1425
02:02:47,408 --> 02:02:52,654
Three men in Malta have been charged with murdering the anti-corruption journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia.

1426
02:02:53,054 --> 02:02:55,377
She was killed in a car bomb attack in October.

1427
02:02:55,777 --> 02:02:59,261
The case has shocked the small Mediterranean island and the European Union.

1428
02:02:59,621 --> 02:03:02,304
The three accused men were among ten arrested on Monday.

1429
02:03:03,445 --> 02:03:05,407
World News from the BBC.

1430
02:03:09,458 --> 02:03:14,860
Fifteen thousand people a day are being forced to flee their homes in African conflict and disaster zones.

1431
02:03:15,400 --> 02:03:24,163
Figures published by the Norwegian Refugee Council and the Internal Deplacement Monitoring Centre show that more than 12 million people in Africa are internally displaced.

1432
02:03:24,623 --> 02:03:30,045
Nearly four million left their homes last year, a quarter of them in the Democratic Republic of Congo alone.

1433
02:03:31,225 --> 02:03:40,970
The opposition in Honduras has demanded a full recount of presidential election ballot papers, which it says were tampered with in order to favor President Juan Orlando Hernández.

1434
02:03:41,470 --> 02:03:47,573
The electoral tribunal had already agreed to an earlier opposition demand to recount around one-third of the ballots.

1435
02:03:48,114 --> 02:03:56,058
The opposition candidate, Salvador Nasralla, has appeared set for victory shortly after the election ten days ago, when the vote count was suddenly halted.

1436
02:03:57,385 --> 02:04:07,908
Christine Keeler, the British former model whose relationships with a British minister and a Soviet diplomat in the 1960s caused one of the most notorious political scandals of the Cold War, has died.

1437
02:04:08,369 --> 02:04:09,449
She was 75.

1438
02:04:09,989 --> 02:04:15,411
As a teenager, she had a brief affair with John Profumo, a senior Cabot member who was forced to resign.

1439
02:04:15,891 --> 02:04:17,792
The scandal rocked the British establishment.

1440
02:04:18,192 --> 02:04:21,933
Christine Keeler said she'd been too young to deal with the impact of the affair.

1441
02:04:22,715 --> 02:04:35,775
I wish that at that time I had been older so that I would have been able to have answered or spoke up for myself, but I was only a young girl.

1442
02:04:36,765 --> 02:04:44,230
Britain's most prestigious contemporary art award, the Turner Prize, has been won by an art professor who was born in Zanzibar, Lubaina Hameed.

1443
02:04:44,730 --> 02:04:54,157
Judges praised her work, which explores the African diaspora and black creativity, for what they called its exuberant approach to painting and its sense of theatre and satire.

1444
02:04:54,557 --> 02:04:58,540
Professor Hameed is the first black woman and the oldest person to win the award.

1445
02:04:58,880 --> 02:05:04,324
She said she would use the $33,000 prize money to help young artists get their work exhibited.

1446
02:05:04,884 --> 02:05:05,665
BBC News.

1447
02:05:08,417 --> 02:05:08,997
Thanks very much.

1448
02:05:09,017 --> 02:05:13,138
You're listening to the Newsroom from the BBC World Service with Oliver Conway.

1449
02:05:13,619 --> 02:05:20,881
Despite warnings from Arab leaders about the possible dangerous repercussions, it seems Donald Trump is planning to move the U.S.

1450
02:05:20,961 --> 02:05:24,102
embassy in Israel from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.

1451
02:05:24,662 --> 02:05:37,853
White House officials have briefed journalists that the president will announce in a speech at 18 Hours GMT on Wednesday that the US is recognising Jerusalem as Israel's capital, making it the first and only country to do so.

1452
02:05:37,873 --> 02:05:40,655
Here's his press secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders.

1453
02:05:41,248 --> 02:05:45,310
Finally, I know there have been a lot of questions surrounding the President's decision on Jerusalem.

1454
02:05:45,770 --> 02:05:47,651
Tomorrow, the President will deliver remarks.

1455
02:05:48,251 --> 02:05:52,453
Has the President made up his mind about this, or is this decision still in flux?

1456
02:05:53,514 --> 02:05:58,176
The President, I would say, is pretty solid in his thinking at this point.

1457
02:05:58,976 --> 02:06:05,201
Both the Palestinians and the Israelis claim Jerusalem as a capital of any current or future state.

1458
02:06:05,721 --> 02:06:15,208
President Trump has tried to ease concerns with a series of phone calls to Arab leaders in the Middle East, including the Palestinian leader, as we heard from Yolande Nel in Jerusalem.

1459
02:06:15,878 --> 02:06:21,902
In their phone call, the Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas is said to have warned Mr Trump that moving the U.S.

1460
02:06:22,002 --> 02:06:26,946
embassy would have an impact on the peace process with Israel and regional stability.

1461
02:06:27,486 --> 02:06:34,031
Mr Abbas has since spoken to the Pope and the leaders of Russia, France and Jordan, asking them to intervene.

1462
02:06:34,671 --> 02:06:42,097
King Abdullah of Jordan was also called by Mr Trump and is said to have spoken of possible dangerous repercussions of his plan.

1463
02:06:42,877 --> 02:06:48,741
Egypt's President Sisi is reported to have told him there was no need to complicate matters in the Middle East.

1464
02:07:00,348 --> 02:07:12,976
Well yes, although with the caveat that unless until he actually delivers the speech we can't predict entirely what he's going to say and specifically his thinking behind this decision.

1465
02:07:13,416 --> 02:07:24,183
It would be highly contentious, it already is, in terms of what we have heard in moving the embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem effectively

1466
02:07:24,603 --> 02:07:39,088
acknowledging Jerusalem as the capital of Israel, the first country to do so since the foundation of the state of Israel since 1948, and it would mark a sea change in certainly US policy towards the region.

1467
02:07:39,608 --> 02:07:46,810
And the briefings we're getting from White House officials suggest though that it will take some time to move the embassy.

1468
02:07:49,174 --> 02:08:00,719
Yes, what we understand is that there will be some form of waiver written into Mr Trump's announcement that will keep the embassy in Tel Aviv for at least six months.

1469
02:08:00,799 --> 02:08:16,105
Now, my understanding is that much of this is simply logistics, the moving of staff between the two cities, which is clearly going to take some time, but perhaps also it is a little bit of breathing space to see what the reaction

1470
02:08:16,685 --> 02:08:25,293
is going to be and the policy may well change over coming months depending on how things unravel in the weeks and months to come.

1471
02:08:25,594 --> 02:08:28,857
And why, what is the attraction of doing this for President Trump?

1472
02:08:31,170 --> 02:08:51,649
Well, certainly it was part of his campaign pledge that he wanted to do this and it was one of his major foreign policy planks and perhaps domestic policy comes into this a little bit in terms of the president wanting to be seen to be making good on those big promises in his first year.

1473
02:08:51,709 --> 02:08:54,832
I mentioned domestic politics because it hasn't necessarily all gone his way.

1474
02:08:55,232 --> 02:08:56,693
in terms of those big promises.

1475
02:08:56,753 --> 02:09:02,937
So I think he wants to get something done, and I think he is known as quite an impatient character in this respect.

1476
02:09:03,218 --> 02:09:10,423
But in terms of doing it now, I think there are quite a few people here who are rather mystified by the timing.

1477
02:09:10,563 --> 02:09:14,886
We know that the White House, the Trump administration, has been working on a peace plan for several months.

1478
02:09:14,966 --> 02:09:16,607
We don't know the detail of that.

1479
02:09:17,047 --> 02:09:44,260
So why to make this announcement now, perhaps ahead of a bigger plan and bigger negotiations, I think we remain to see, because it does show the US's hand, and if the US is going to play a role as a mediator in negotiations between the Palestinians and the Israelis, it perhaps makes things rather awkward, because it's certainly not what the Palestinians wanted to hear.

1480
02:09:44,760 --> 02:09:45,782
Peter, many thanks indeed.

1481
02:09:46,022 --> 02:09:53,956
Peter Bowes there and hopefully we'll get more details in that speech apparently from Donald Trump tomorrow at lunchtime in the US.

1482
02:09:55,000 --> 02:09:57,622
While he focuses on that big change in U.S.

1483
02:09:57,762 --> 02:10:03,046
foreign policy, Donald Trump could be facing an investigation at home into his finances.

1484
02:10:03,587 --> 02:10:06,669
I say could because there's some dispute over whether the U.S.

1485
02:10:06,689 --> 02:10:12,414
special counsel Robert Mueller has issued a subpoena for Mr. Trump's financial records at Deutsche Bank.

1486
02:10:13,014 --> 02:10:14,455
Many media outlets in the U.S.

1487
02:10:14,495 --> 02:10:21,361
reported that he had, but it was denied by the president's legal team, as relayed by White House Press Secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders.

1488
02:10:21,905 --> 02:10:38,273
Look, I think it's important to note, and hopefully you guys have seen this statement, that Jay Sekulow, a member of the president's legal team, has put out within the last hour that they confirmed that the news reports that the special counsel had subpoenaed financial records relating to the president are completely false.

1489
02:10:38,713 --> 02:10:40,714
No subpoena has been issued or received.

1490
02:10:41,054 --> 02:10:43,355
We've confirmed this with the bank and other sources.

1491
02:10:43,695 --> 02:10:49,758
I think that this is another example of the media going too far too fast, and we don't see it going in that direction.

1492
02:10:50,378 --> 02:10:53,540
So, do we know if a subpoena has indeed been issued?

1493
02:10:53,580 --> 02:10:56,661
A question for our correspondent Anthony Zerke in Washington.

1494
02:10:57,081 --> 02:10:57,441
We don't.

1495
02:10:57,521 --> 02:11:07,286
We had multiple news outlets reporting that the documents had been subpoenaed by the special counsel Robert Mueller, subpoenaing Deutsche Bank.

1496
02:11:07,446 --> 02:11:14,189
But since then, the White House lawyers have pushed back fairly vociferously, saying there was no subpoena request.

1497
02:11:14,549 --> 02:11:18,371
They checked with Deutsche Bank and other sources that have

1498
02:11:19,071 --> 02:11:25,858
said these reports are false, but the sources that these news outlets are citing are standing by their contention.

1499
02:11:25,939 --> 02:11:31,284
So it's basically up in the air whether this actually has happened or not.

1500
02:11:31,524 --> 02:11:34,828
And why would the special counsel want those records?

1501
02:11:35,228 --> 02:11:44,692
Well, that's the interesting thing here, because so far Robert Mueller has, say, looked into the foreign lobbying of Paul Manafort, Donald Trump's former campaign chair.

1502
02:11:44,712 --> 02:11:56,718
He has reached a plea agreement with Michael Flynn, who was a confidant of Donald Trump's and his first national security adviser, and George Papadopoulos, who was a foreign policy adviser on the campaign.

1503
02:11:56,878 --> 02:12:05,083
Those are all kind of outside the main purview of the inspection of whether there's ties between the Trump campaign and Russian meddling.

1504
02:12:05,103 --> 02:12:18,831
Well, here you have Robert Mueller directly looking at the president himself, if it's true, and his finances, looking at Deutsche Bank, because Donald Trump owes Deutsche Bank about $300 million when he came into the presidency.

1505
02:12:19,231 --> 02:12:28,556
The bank has loaned Donald Trump about $4 billion over the course of the past 20 years, so they have very close financial ties.

1506
02:12:29,096 --> 02:12:36,800
And this all raises the question of whether Robert Mueller will be allowed to continue his investigation.

1507
02:12:37,662 --> 02:12:53,537
Well, when Donald Trump was interviewed about this a few months back, they asked whether it would be a red line, whether it would be going too far beyond his mandate if Robert Mueller started looking into his business dealings prior to being a presidential candidate.

1508
02:12:54,137 --> 02:13:03,266
And Donald Trump was fairly clear that he thought that would be going too far, and perhaps this would instigate a more aggressive response from the president.

1509
02:13:03,726 --> 02:13:16,032
possibly even trying to get rid of Robert Mueller, which, as president, he could do if he orders people in his Justice Department to do so, although that would create quite a controversy.

1510
02:13:16,172 --> 02:13:27,558
But there may be some uneasiness on the part of Donald Trump to having someone poking around in his business dealings long before he was a serious candidate for political office.

1511
02:13:28,098 --> 02:13:30,039
Anthony Zerker in Washington.

1512
02:13:30,680 --> 02:13:40,506
Let's go across now to Los Angeles, because since wildfires started there just over a day ago, the flames have spread across some 180 square kilometres.

1513
02:13:41,107 --> 02:13:52,654
People in California have already experienced a number of bad wildfires this year, but now 27,000 residents have suddenly been forced to evacuate, with no sign of when the fires will be put out.

1514
02:13:53,175 --> 02:13:54,556
James Cook is in LA.

1515
02:13:55,356 --> 02:14:02,221
This wildfire exploded overnight, trembling in size in just a few hours, driven by ferocious Santa Ana winds.

1516
02:14:04,662 --> 02:14:07,244
Devastation, with nothing to salvage.

1517
02:14:08,064 --> 02:14:11,887
Families had just minutes to scramble their belongings together and flee.

1518
02:14:13,008 --> 02:14:18,011
Good friends up the street lost their homes, and I'm just so sad for them.

1519
02:14:18,071 --> 02:14:23,935
I'm happy for myself and those of us that kept their homes, but it's awful.

1520
02:14:26,240 --> 02:14:28,222
There is, though, little hope of the winds easing.

1521
02:14:28,522 --> 02:14:32,846
They are dry, gusty and erratic, the most dangerous conditions possible.

1522
02:14:33,667 --> 02:14:42,094
Ventura is home to more than 100,000 people, and with more than 1,000 firefighters struggling to protect the city, a second blaze broke out.

1523
02:14:42,775 --> 02:14:49,341
This fire is closer to L.A., and millions of Angelenos awoke to find the skies to the north thick with smoke.

1524
02:14:51,239 --> 02:14:56,382
Helicopters have struggled to fly in the wind, making it much harder to contain the fires.

1525
02:14:57,023 --> 02:15:03,787
With forecasters warning that the dangerous weather will continue for several days, the governor of California declared an emergency.

1526
02:15:04,287 --> 02:15:11,272
And with a third fire now burning, the most devastating wildfire season on record in this state just got a lot worse.

1527
02:15:11,952 --> 02:15:14,274
James Cook reporting from Los Angeles.

1528
02:15:14,294 --> 02:15:17,257
Quick bit of breaking news from France.

1529
02:15:17,317 --> 02:15:26,446
The country's best-known rock star, Johnny Hallyday, often known as the French Elvis, has died at the age of 74 after a battle with lung cancer.

1530
02:15:26,466 --> 02:15:29,589
And we'll bring you more on that before the end of the programme.

1531
02:15:29,709 --> 02:15:32,191
This is the Newsroom from the BBC World Service.

1532
02:15:32,572 --> 02:15:33,573
Gareth has our headlines.

1533
02:15:34,191 --> 02:15:41,098
Senior officials in the Trump administration say the United States will recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel later on Wednesday.

1534
02:15:41,719 --> 02:15:45,422
Tens of thousands of Californians have fled wildfires north of Los Angeles.

1535
02:15:45,903 --> 02:15:52,309
And there's been a furious reaction in Moscow after the International Olympic Committee banned Russia from the forthcoming Winter Olympics.

1536
02:15:52,689 --> 02:15:56,053
Yes, this was state TV in Russia announcing the news.

1537
02:15:56,668 --> 02:16:07,072
The International Olympic Committee announced the decision after a 17-month investigation into allegations of state-sponsored doping at the 2014 Games in the Russian city of Sochi.

1538
02:16:18,436 --> 02:16:29,021
Some Russian athletes will be able to compete in 2018 as neutral competitors under the Olympic flag, but Russia's Olympic Committee says it will appeal against the ban.

1539
02:16:29,201 --> 02:16:31,662
For reaction from Moscow, we heard from Steve Rosenberg.

1540
02:16:32,082 --> 02:16:40,746
There's a sense of deep disappointment here, a sense of injustice too, and an unwillingness to accept that Russia has committed a crime here.

1541
02:16:41,267 --> 02:16:43,808
The Deputy Speaker of the Russian Parliament, Igor Lebedev,

1542
02:16:44,228 --> 02:16:46,690
said this was a humiliation for our country.

1543
02:16:47,050 --> 02:16:49,312
I spoke to Dmitry Svishchev.

1544
02:16:49,612 --> 02:16:53,215
He's a Russian MP and the president of Russia's Curling Federation.

1545
02:16:53,255 --> 02:16:56,358
He told me this was unjust, not based on any evidence.

1546
02:16:56,758 --> 02:16:59,220
He said collective responsibility was unfair.

1547
02:16:59,960 --> 02:17:04,702
He suggested this was a political decision and said sport should be outside of politics.

1548
02:17:04,722 --> 02:17:08,944
And then I went to a ski slope on the edge of Moscow, just to speak to ordinary Muscovites.

1549
02:17:09,204 --> 02:17:10,985
First of all, it's a political decision.

1550
02:17:11,325 --> 02:17:19,308
It's a very bad decision and I disagree with the position of the World Olympic Committee and so on.

1551
02:17:19,968 --> 02:17:28,415
because I think that for Russian sportsmen it will be great and very important to show their results under the Russian flag.

1552
02:17:28,796 --> 02:17:45,370
In recent weeks a number of Russian politicians have suggested that if the IOC was to take that decision and allow clean Russian sportsmen to take part under the Olympic flag that they should not do so, that this would be almost treachery on the part of the sportsmen.

1553
02:17:45,930 --> 02:17:47,952
Everything will depend, I think, on what

1554
02:17:48,572 --> 02:18:01,717
Vladimir Putin says, because there is one man who will decide this question, that is the Russian president, and we expect that he will announce his decision on whether Russian sportsmen should go and take part under the neutrofag.

1555
02:18:02,077 --> 02:18:06,919
This will decide what kind of participation there will be from Russia in the Olympic Games.

1556
02:18:07,439 --> 02:18:09,581
Steve Rosenberg in Moscow.

1557
02:18:10,602 --> 02:18:17,667
Eastern Ghouta, a suburb of the Syrian capital Damascus, has faced unrelenting bombardment in the past three weeks.

1558
02:18:18,328 --> 02:18:22,211
A ceasefire announced recently didn't even hold for a full 24 hours.

1559
02:18:22,852 --> 02:18:28,876
As the death toll from airstrikes continues to rise, so does the number of children nearing starvation.

1560
02:18:29,317 --> 02:18:36,723
The UN has said that acute malnutrition among youngsters is at the highest level recorded anywhere in Syria since the war there began.

1561
02:18:37,123 --> 02:18:39,544
Martin Patience reports now from Eastern Ghouta.

1562
02:18:42,686 --> 02:18:47,368
The aftermath of the latest airstrikes is like a scene from hell.

1563
02:18:48,089 --> 02:18:54,432
The sky is dark with dust and debris as rescuers rush into buildings to scoop up children.

1564
02:18:55,493 --> 02:18:58,714
Among the injured was five-year-old Yusuf with a head wound.

1565
02:18:59,435 --> 02:19:05,098
The doctors patch him up as best they can, but they're desperately short of medical supplies.

1566
02:19:08,315 --> 02:19:15,409
A rebel stronghold, Eastern Rota, has been bombed and besieged by the Syrian government for several years.

1567
02:19:16,371 --> 02:19:19,297
Many families are now on the brink of starvation.

1568
02:19:22,186 --> 02:19:27,568
Eight-year-old Noor and his seven-year-old sister, Ghazal, sit round a wood-burning oven.

1569
02:19:28,469 --> 02:19:36,693
It's their first and only meal of the day, a thin piece of bread made from barley, which is normally fed to donkeys.

1570
02:19:37,813 --> 02:19:42,355
Their father, Abu Ahmed, was seriously injured when out gathering firewood.

1571
02:19:44,812 --> 02:19:47,835
A shell landed close to me, and I was hit by a shrapnel.

1572
02:19:47,955 --> 02:19:52,178
I was blinded in my left eye, and my knee was damaged, and I can no longer walk.

1573
02:19:52,379 --> 02:19:57,423
I'm in a pretty bad shape, and I have three kids to look after.

1574
02:19:58,444 --> 02:20:01,486
That means his children are left carrying the burden.

1575
02:20:02,027 --> 02:20:04,169
Here, they're fetching drinking water.

1576
02:20:05,230 --> 02:20:11,015
It's no surprise, then, that Ghazal dreams of freeing herself from her prison, Eastern Ghouta.

1577
02:20:12,540 --> 02:20:17,526
I wish I could have cookies, sweeties, or any other delicious foods.

1578
02:20:17,546 --> 02:20:23,533
And I wish someone could send me a pair of slippers and some new clothes and shoes.

1579
02:20:24,133 --> 02:20:28,639
I really miss food, like chicken, cheese, tea, and juice.

1580
02:20:34,802 --> 02:20:40,204
In another home, two-and-a-half-year-old Hamza is suffering from severe malnutrition.

1581
02:20:41,044 --> 02:20:45,905
His ribs are protruding, and he's wearing a plastic bag as a nappy.

1582
02:20:46,965 --> 02:20:49,906
He was abandoned before being taken in by a neighbour.

1583
02:20:51,187 --> 02:20:56,188
Umm Mohammed says Hamza is like one of her children.

1584
02:20:56,888 --> 02:20:58,889
He's my son now, she says.

1585
02:21:02,610 --> 02:21:05,733
There's supposed to be a ceasefire in Eastern Ghouta.

1586
02:21:06,333 --> 02:21:09,956
But almost every day, people in this area dig fresh graves.

1587
02:21:10,717 --> 02:21:13,680
For families here, there's no respite from the war.

1588
02:21:15,390 --> 02:21:18,191
Our report from eastern Utah by Martin Patience.

1589
02:21:18,391 --> 02:21:20,172
And now Gareth has some more of the day's stories.

1590
02:21:20,712 --> 02:21:27,115
One of Australia's most prominent churchmen is going on trial today accused of covering up child abuse in the 1970s.

1591
02:21:27,595 --> 02:21:33,598
The Archbishop of Adelaide, Philip Watson, is the most senior Catholic figure in the world to be charged with this type of offence.

1592
02:21:34,378 --> 02:21:38,360
A military operation in Western Cameroon has led to hundreds of people fleeing their villages.

1593
02:21:38,920 --> 02:21:46,086
The exodus comes after the government pledged to retaliate against an armed group that wants independence for the country's two English-speaking regions.

1594
02:21:46,647 --> 02:21:49,449
Some of those fleeing the army have crossed into neighboring Nigeria.

1595
02:21:50,310 --> 02:21:58,998
The public prosecutor in Saudi Arabia has said that most of those detained in an unprecedented anti-corruption purge have agreed to settlements in order to avoid prosecution.

1596
02:21:59,438 --> 02:22:05,763
He said that a total of 320 people have so far been subpoenaed to provide information about alleged corruption.

1597
02:22:06,604 --> 02:22:15,169
Ukraine's prosecutor general says Georgia's former president, Mikhail Saakashvili, has 24 hours to hand himself over to the Ukrainian authorities.

1598
02:22:15,869 --> 02:22:19,551
Mr Saakashvili was invited to Ukraine by its president, Petro Poroshenko.

1599
02:22:20,012 --> 02:22:24,955
But the two men have fallen out, and Mr Saakashvili has become a prominent opposition politician.

1600
02:22:25,495 --> 02:22:34,400
On Tuesday, Mr Saakashvili's supporters helped him escape from security officers in dramatic scenes, as our correspondent in Kiev, Jonah Fisher, reports.

1601
02:22:36,965 --> 02:22:41,067
This was a remarkable day in the extraordinary career of Mikhail Saakashvili.

1602
02:22:41,547 --> 02:22:44,909
It started on the roof of his apartment block in central Kiev.

1603
02:22:45,329 --> 02:22:50,532
He spoke to his supporters below as security agents climbed up the stairs to arrest him.

1604
02:22:51,092 --> 02:23:03,818
Then, having been detained, Saakashvili's supporters first blockaded, then hours later broke open the police van he was inside, enabling the former Georgian president to escape triumphantly.

1605
02:23:05,699 --> 02:23:08,400
What happens next?

1606
02:23:08,640 --> 02:23:11,282
We will go now to Parliament.

1607
02:23:11,582 --> 02:23:13,043
We will go to Parliament.

1608
02:23:13,103 --> 02:23:13,843
What happens next?

1609
02:23:13,863 --> 02:23:20,287
We will ask for impeachment of Poroshenko, who is a thief, who is mega-corrupt, who is plundering the entire Ukraine with his gang.

1610
02:23:20,387 --> 02:23:25,990
We have to stop supporting him, because it's outrageous what they are up to.

1611
02:23:26,070 --> 02:23:28,851
And today it was a classical political arrest.

1612
02:23:28,891 --> 02:23:31,773
Do you think you really have the support of the people here in your bank?

1613
02:23:31,793 --> 02:23:32,593
Absolutely.

1614
02:23:32,654 --> 02:23:33,414
You saw it today.

1615
02:23:33,774 --> 02:23:42,986
Ukraine's Prosecutor General says Mr. Saakashvili should be detained for allegedly receiving funds from businessmen connected to the former President Viktor Yanukovych.

1616
02:23:43,527 --> 02:23:51,496
Mr. Saakashvili says he's being targeted for his increasingly vocal campaign against Ukraine's President Petro Poroshenko.

1617
02:23:52,077 --> 02:23:57,684
It was Mr Poroshenko who granted Mr Saakashvili Ukrainian citizenship in 2015.

1618
02:23:58,144 --> 02:24:05,572
But the relationship soured as Mr Saakashvili accused his former friend of not being serious about tackling corruption.

1619
02:24:06,113 --> 02:24:07,434
Jonah Fisher in Ukraine.

1620
02:24:08,015 --> 02:24:13,921
There's been political chaos and protest in Honduras since the presidential election on November 26th.

1621
02:24:14,441 --> 02:24:27,214
The opposition has now demanded a full recount of the votes, which ended up in favour of the incumbent president, Juan Orlando Hernández, after initially looking promising for the opposition candidate and former TV star Salvador Nasralla.

1622
02:24:27,734 --> 02:24:30,197
Candace Peards, our America's editor, told me the latest.

1623
02:24:30,765 --> 02:24:38,050
They haven't declared a winner yet and now what we're seeing is the opposition are now demanding a full recount of the vote.

1624
02:24:38,150 --> 02:24:39,391
Now why are they doing this?

1625
02:24:40,012 --> 02:24:53,902
Earlier the electoral tribunal had agreed to a partial recount of around a third of all the ballot papers in the elections and now it looks like the opposition have taken this opportunity to extend their demand even further.

1626
02:24:54,042 --> 02:24:55,403
They might have been emboldened by

1627
02:24:55,943 --> 02:24:58,644
very recent, quite surprising events.

1628
02:24:59,204 --> 02:25:13,349
On Monday, hundreds of members of the riot police refused to carry out orders to enforce a nighttime curfew ordered by the government to keep order after widespread street protests organized by the opposition.

1629
02:25:13,809 --> 02:25:19,551
Now, the police spokesman said they didn't want to clamp down on peaceful protest.

1630
02:25:20,091 --> 02:25:29,496
It's really unusual in Latin America to see ordinary voters out on the streets, as we saw on Tuesday, holding placards thanking the riot police.

1631
02:25:30,316 --> 02:25:46,104
And then the opposition also had support from international observers, who've been urging the Supreme Electoral Tribunal to agree to a wider recount, arguing there'd be numerous inconsistencies, including ballot boxes that arrived opened or incomplete.

1632
02:25:46,244 --> 02:25:47,465
So is it possible we could get

1633
02:25:48,205 --> 02:25:50,826
a full recount or even a rerun of the election?

1634
02:25:51,766 --> 02:25:58,929
That's certainly something that the opposition, Salvador Nasralla and the opposition coalition are calling for.

1635
02:25:58,989 --> 02:26:09,193
They're calling now for a very wide recount, 18,000 ballot boxes, and he has already been tweeting about possibly it would be better to have a full election again.

1636
02:26:09,693 --> 02:26:14,058
Candace Peart said on the news that Johnny Alliday, the French rocker, has died at the age of 74.

1637
02:26:14,098 --> 02:26:19,764
He sold more than 110 million records and made 30 films.

1638
02:26:19,784 --> 02:26:23,607
Yet outside the French-speaking world, he was virtually unknown.

1639
02:26:23,748 --> 02:26:25,770
