2623
04:05:31,610 --> 04:05:36,193
It links two men in ways that are both disturbing and inspiring.

2624
04:05:36,293 --> 04:05:37,674
Both were child soldiers in the 1980s

2625
04:05:38,795 --> 04:05:40,096
in Sudan's civil war.

2626
04:05:40,616 --> 04:05:43,917
The younger of them, Ayik Shute, was just 13 when he took up arms.

2627
04:05:44,317 --> 04:05:50,200
He did it because his father, brother and grandmother had all been killed and he wanted to fight back.

2628
04:05:50,440 --> 04:05:55,422
So he joined the Sudan People's Liberation Army and was sent to a training camp in Ethiopia.

2629
04:05:56,062 --> 04:05:57,523
The first few weeks was all right.

2630
04:05:58,613 --> 04:06:00,074
And then it just got worse.

2631
04:06:00,114 --> 04:06:01,215
We're getting trained.

2632
04:06:01,896 --> 04:06:03,557
It's on, like, Ethiopian mountain.

2633
04:06:03,998 --> 04:06:05,379
So we just climb up there.

2634
04:06:05,499 --> 04:06:09,162
Even if you're thirsty, you can't go to the river by yourselves.

2635
04:06:09,202 --> 04:06:11,945
When the boss say we got to go and drink, that's when you got to go.

2636
04:06:12,325 --> 04:06:15,308
It's like the old age, the stone age, you know?

2637
04:06:16,048 --> 04:06:18,249
Everything, we used to use rocks to cut trees.

2638
04:06:18,750 --> 04:06:19,490
So it's hard work.

2639
04:06:19,690 --> 04:06:22,492
And what were you expected to do apart from that?

2640
04:06:22,892 --> 04:06:24,213
Just getting trained every day.

2641
04:06:24,233 --> 04:06:24,833
That's it.

2642
04:06:25,113 --> 04:06:26,254
Do what the boss say.

2643
04:06:26,354 --> 04:06:29,776
In the morning, wake up around 4 o'clock or 5 o'clock in the morning.

2644
04:06:30,436 --> 04:06:32,237
You go until 12 o'clock.

2645
04:06:32,597 --> 04:06:35,119
Just getting trained in the mountain with using a stick.

2646
04:06:35,780 --> 04:06:36,721
to haul it like a gun.

2647
04:06:37,341 --> 04:06:41,124
You know, how you attack when you make ambush, all that sort of thing.

2648
04:06:41,184 --> 04:06:44,066
And it was just too much running on the mountain, no water.

2649
04:06:44,686 --> 04:06:47,228
And you only eat once in the morning, and that's it.

2650
04:06:47,468 --> 04:06:48,069
What would you eat?

2651
04:06:48,409 --> 04:06:48,789
Corn.

2652
04:06:48,809 --> 04:06:50,490
We used to boil corn or rice.

2653
04:06:51,391 --> 04:06:54,473
And then we make our own soup or whatever.

2654
04:06:54,493 --> 04:06:59,977
We're going to get some tree leaves somewhere, because we're all from different part of Sudan.

2655
04:07:00,317 --> 04:07:04,580
So when I came there, you learn to eat other food from other cultures.

2656
04:07:05,504 --> 04:07:08,965
You know, other culture that were there with me, other children that were there with me.

2657
04:07:09,145 --> 04:07:13,947
When you graduated, as it were, from sticks to guns, what was expected of you?

2658
04:07:14,827 --> 04:07:15,587
Just get a fight.

2659
04:07:16,047 --> 04:07:16,427
That was it.

2660
04:07:16,747 --> 04:07:17,408
And would you fight?

2661
04:07:18,308 --> 04:07:18,688
Yeah.

2662
04:07:20,189 --> 04:07:21,589
I've been attacked so many times.

2663
04:07:21,789 --> 04:07:23,610
And I've seen people dying.

2664
04:07:23,630 --> 04:07:24,970
It's too much.

2665
04:07:24,990 --> 04:07:27,971
When I used to think of them, I used to cry.

2666
04:07:28,071 --> 04:07:31,172
And then after a while, I think it's fading.

2667
04:07:32,874 --> 04:07:37,738
The memories is there but it's not as bad as I used to think because I'm grown up now.

2668
04:07:38,059 --> 04:07:39,840
But the punishment was so bad.

2669
04:07:40,401 --> 04:07:46,566
The punishment was to be sent to a prison at the camp where another child soldier called Anyang had been put in charge.

2670
04:07:47,167 --> 04:07:50,750
He and the other young prison guards were known to torture the boys.

2671
04:07:51,490 --> 04:07:58,857
Sometimes you have to stand on one feet and every time you take the ground with the other feet you got four people around you that would just whip you

2672
04:08:00,487 --> 04:08:02,789
And sometimes you get tied up, like hogtie.

2673
04:08:03,289 --> 04:08:04,611
You're only sitting on your chest.

2674
04:08:04,631 --> 04:08:08,414
They'll just leave you there for hours, six, seven hours tied up.

2675
04:08:08,815 --> 04:08:10,897
You know, the skin does peel off a little bit.

2676
04:08:11,618 --> 04:08:15,061
And when you see the skin peel off, he'll put chili in it.

2677
04:08:15,081 --> 04:08:16,923
He'll just rub chili in it.

2678
04:08:18,395 --> 04:08:30,865
And he'd done it, he'd done it to another child, so I was there with me, and he was tired after so long, and chile was put there, and got infected, and then the doctors couldn't do anything about it, so ended up getting amputated.

2679
04:08:31,466 --> 04:08:33,447
You had chile rubbed in your wounds as well, did you?

2680
04:08:33,828 --> 04:08:35,569
Yeah, yeah, yeah, it happened to me all the time.

2681
04:08:35,629 --> 04:08:38,772
Can you even describe what that feels like?

2682
04:08:39,332 --> 04:08:42,955
All I remember, I cry, then you can't cry anymore, you know what I mean?

2683
04:08:44,512 --> 04:08:47,313
You know, you want to, and your lunk is gone.

2684
04:08:47,333 --> 04:08:48,854
There's nothing that can come out of it.

2685
04:08:49,434 --> 04:08:54,637
Anyang, Iyik's torturer, was a child himself, just a few years older than his prisoner.

2686
04:08:55,397 --> 04:08:59,679
I know that he was just bigger than me, and he had the power.

2687
04:08:59,899 --> 04:09:05,021
When you would see Anyang, what kind of emotions would come to you?

2688
04:09:05,842 --> 04:09:06,842
Back then, there's nothing.

2689
04:09:07,082 --> 04:09:10,924
I'd just stand up and just salute him, because that was it.

2690
04:09:11,084 --> 04:09:12,885
I was useless at the time, but inside,

2691
04:09:13,619 --> 04:09:15,900
I used to pray that I want to get deployed with them.

2692
04:09:16,461 --> 04:09:17,562
I want to go to war with them.

2693
04:09:18,322 --> 04:09:19,323
That was my prayer.

2694
04:09:19,363 --> 04:09:20,543
That was what I used to pray for.

2695
04:09:20,924 --> 04:09:21,144
Why?

2696
04:09:22,144 --> 04:09:23,545
Because I wanted to kill them.

2697
04:09:24,626 --> 04:09:26,207
So bad, so bad.

2698
04:09:26,227 --> 04:09:32,031
You know, no one has ever, ever, ever put me through what I went through in the rebel.

2699
04:09:32,391 --> 04:09:35,553
No one has ever, ever beat me up like Aung San Suu Kyi did.

2700
04:09:36,365 --> 04:09:44,107
Ayik kept trying to run away and each time was caught and punished by Anyang until he'd finished his training and was sent off to fight.

2701
04:09:44,127 --> 04:09:55,631
Ayik was on the front lines for four years before his older sister managed to get him away to Kenya to a refugee camp and to his joy he and his relatives were granted a visa to go and live in Australia.

2702
04:09:57,532 --> 04:09:58,652
The first night we came here

2703
04:09:59,817 --> 04:10:01,078
Oh, man, the sausages.

2704
04:10:01,458 --> 04:10:04,721
And I have never eaten so many sausages in my life until I came here.

2705
04:10:05,081 --> 04:10:05,942
I even threw up.

2706
04:10:06,623 --> 04:10:11,907
I went there, threw up, and then came and ate, because I was thinking, maybe this is just, they're doing it for tonight.

2707
04:10:12,367 --> 04:10:14,209
Tomorrow is going to be just the same.

2708
04:10:14,249 --> 04:10:15,710
We wouldn't be treated like visitors.

2709
04:10:16,210 --> 04:10:20,614
And then the next day, I wake up in the morning, there's breakfast, again, sausages.

2710
04:10:21,374 --> 04:10:22,815
I don't even eat sausages anymore.

2711
04:10:22,835 --> 04:10:23,756
I hate sausages.

2712
04:10:24,116 --> 04:10:25,117
You overdosed on them.

2713
04:10:25,597 --> 04:10:26,298
Yeah, I think.

2714
04:10:26,358 --> 04:10:27,019
I think I did.

2715
04:10:28,336 --> 04:10:30,277
What else did you like about Australia?

2716
04:10:31,138 --> 04:10:33,360
Oh, it's just that you'd be able to sleep.

2717
04:10:33,380 --> 04:10:35,202
You wouldn't hear a gun.

2718
04:10:35,762 --> 04:10:41,748
The first time I heard fireworks, being an ex-child soldier, when I hear bang, bang, I'm just scared.

2719
04:10:41,848 --> 04:10:43,209
I'm looking around, what's going on?

2720
04:10:43,569 --> 04:10:47,092
And then my brother's little nephew says, yeah, it's the fireworks.

2721
04:10:47,453 --> 04:10:49,715
They were kids, and I just get used to it.

2722
04:10:50,176 --> 04:10:52,723
If I hear a gun now, I probably wouldn't even think it's a gun.

2723
04:10:52,763 --> 04:10:53,966
I'd probably think it's a firework.

2724
04:10:54,307 --> 04:10:56,553
You have the most amazing Australian accent.

2725
04:10:56,774 --> 04:10:57,897
I mean, you really have.

2726
04:10:59,382 --> 04:11:00,343
become Australian, huh?

2727
04:11:01,043 --> 04:11:02,304
Oh, not really.

2728
04:11:02,764 --> 04:11:06,307
Maybe because you're a Pommie, that's why you think I sound like an Aussie.

2729
04:11:06,327 --> 04:11:11,691
But if you hear, if you live in Australia, you probably think, nah, I don't even know my accent.

2730
04:11:11,971 --> 04:11:14,092
You go to church in Australia, in Brisbane?

2731
04:11:14,112 --> 04:11:14,953
Yeah, I go to church.

2732
04:11:15,353 --> 04:11:18,775
Tell us about what happened in church a couple of years after you got there.

2733
04:11:19,036 --> 04:11:20,697
A few years ago, I went to church.

2734
04:11:21,557 --> 04:11:22,378
I think it was a wedding.

2735
04:11:23,232 --> 04:11:25,293
I knew a few people there, hello, how are you doing?

2736
04:11:25,353 --> 04:11:26,534
And then we just had to pray.

2737
04:11:26,854 --> 04:11:32,457
After everything was done, you know when people shake hands, okay, see you Joe, see you Michael.

2738
04:11:32,897 --> 04:11:35,858
And then I look to my right, and I saw this face.

2739
04:11:37,139 --> 04:11:38,980
And I thought, oh no, what's going on?

2740
04:11:39,500 --> 04:11:45,583
And then I look again, and then I realized the face that I was looking at, it was Anyang.

2741
04:11:46,544 --> 04:11:49,846
My mind was telling me, this guy should be dead.

2742
04:11:50,166 --> 04:11:52,587
He should have died back home because I thought

2743
04:11:53,390 --> 04:11:55,835
If someone didn't kill him, who got killed in the war?

2744
04:11:56,416 --> 04:11:57,217
But it was him.

2745
04:11:57,237 --> 04:12:01,646
The moment you saw him, you recognised him as the man who'd run the prison, did you?

2746
04:12:01,786 --> 04:12:03,169
At first I thought it was a flashback.

2747
04:12:04,456 --> 04:12:08,098
And I shook my head like that, wake up, wake up, I was like, what's going on?

2748
04:12:08,158 --> 04:12:10,239
And then I look, I said, oh yeah, that's him.

2749
04:12:10,259 --> 04:12:13,360
I said, oh, this is the guy that used to torture me.

2750
04:12:13,840 --> 04:12:24,605
And this is the guy, every time we run away, he'll send the guard to go and get us, and bring us back there, and then lock us up for up to four weeks, and then release us into training again.

2751
04:12:24,625 --> 04:12:26,346
Oh, this, that's him.

2752
04:12:26,366 --> 04:12:30,428
Okay, I think I should kill him.

2753
04:12:31,448 --> 04:12:32,068
But how?

2754
04:12:32,549 --> 04:12:33,529
And then I start thinking,

2755
04:12:34,550 --> 04:12:37,532
He's in church, and then I'm in Australia.

2756
04:12:37,872 --> 04:12:41,534
If I kill him now, I'll probably get locked up for the rest of my life.

2757
04:12:41,954 --> 04:12:43,595
All these sort of things were going on in my mind.

2758
04:12:43,995 --> 04:12:47,337
And then the time was over anyway, because it was the end of the service.

2759
04:12:47,857 --> 04:12:49,398
And then I never went to that church again.

2760
04:12:50,058 --> 04:12:51,319
Because he might be there?

2761
04:12:52,279 --> 04:12:52,820
Because of him.

2762
04:12:53,260 --> 04:12:55,101
I was very angry, very angry.

2763
04:12:55,929 --> 04:12:58,011
I wanted to kill him, but I just didn't know how to do it.

2764
04:12:58,411 --> 04:13:01,853
You know, if I found him in Africa, I think it would have been a different story.

2765
04:13:01,873 --> 04:13:07,337
If I found him where he had no power and it was in Africa, that's it.

2766
04:13:07,798 --> 04:13:12,441
Did you have anyone in Australia to talk to about it, to talk about your feelings and what you were going through?

2767
04:13:13,263 --> 04:13:15,084
No, I didn't want to talk to no one.

2768
04:13:15,744 --> 04:13:18,265
I just kept it to myself, even my own family.

2769
04:13:18,785 --> 04:13:20,546
My own family didn't even know about it.

2770
04:13:20,906 --> 04:13:25,528
Two years, I think it was, after that church sighting, you see Anyang again.

2771
04:13:25,909 --> 04:13:27,029
What were the circumstances?

2772
04:13:27,269 --> 04:13:29,110
It was at a party, a friend's place.

2773
04:13:30,118 --> 04:13:31,699
And then I was drinking.

2774
04:13:32,239 --> 04:13:34,781
And then when I'm drinking, you know, I'm a happy person.

2775
04:13:35,601 --> 04:13:37,242
I said, hey, how you doing?

2776
04:13:37,663 --> 04:13:39,184
I said, yeah, you remember me?

2777
04:13:39,204 --> 04:13:41,605
And he said, yeah, of course I remember.

2778
04:13:42,245 --> 04:13:45,948
And then I said, man, I swear to God, you're lucky.

2779
04:13:46,428 --> 04:13:47,989
You know, Australia saved your life.

2780
04:13:48,889 --> 04:13:50,951
From there, I went, I left.

2781
04:13:51,411 --> 04:13:52,091
And that was it.

2782
04:13:53,072 --> 04:13:54,453
That was the second time I saw him.

2783
04:13:55,213 --> 04:13:58,215
Ayat, can you introduce the man sitting next to you right now?

2784
04:14:00,223 --> 04:14:01,164
Okay.

2785
04:14:02,386 --> 04:14:09,616
Joe, meet Anyang, Anyang Rang, my ex-boss when I was a child soldier.

2786
04:14:09,636 --> 04:14:11,318
He's here sitting next to me.

2787
04:14:12,159 --> 04:14:12,780
Anyang, hello.

2788
04:14:12,800 --> 04:14:13,982
Hello.

2789
04:14:16,526 --> 04:14:23,710
What can you tell us about seeing Ayik at that party, talking to him, saying you remembered him?

2790
04:14:24,390 --> 04:14:26,231
What went through your head?

2791
04:14:26,832 --> 04:14:32,594
That was not a good meeting at all, to be honest, because you can judge somebody by their look.

2792
04:14:34,235 --> 04:14:39,498
Ayik was coming near to me while he's really, really angry.

2793
04:14:40,913 --> 04:14:44,183
So when I see that way, I didn't wait.

2794
04:14:44,604 --> 04:14:46,168
I walked away from him.

2795
04:14:46,928 --> 04:14:48,529
Well, Ayik couldn't forget about it.

2796
04:14:48,549 --> 04:14:50,049
It preyed on his mind.

2797
04:14:50,269 --> 04:14:56,171
And then he saw an advert for a new television programme on the Australian channel SBS, Look Me In The Eye.

2798
04:14:56,591 --> 04:15:07,075
They were trying to find people who were estranged or had an issue to meet and try to solve their differences through a mediation technique where the parties stare at each other but don't talk, at least at first.

2799
04:15:07,655 --> 04:15:10,516
Ayik applied and was invited onto the show.

2800
04:15:10,536 --> 04:15:12,477
It's like a warehouse.

2801
04:15:12,937 --> 04:15:14,757
There's two seats and that's it.

2802
04:15:15,078 --> 04:15:16,138
So I was sitting there

2803
04:15:16,910 --> 04:15:19,292
And then I can hear footsteps.

2804
04:15:19,392 --> 04:15:20,452
There was someone coming.

2805
04:15:21,393 --> 04:15:23,955
And that person came and sat opposite to me.

2806
04:15:24,135 --> 04:15:28,197
And I had to raise my head and look straight into his eye.

2807
04:15:28,818 --> 04:15:29,818
And that's where we began.

2808
04:15:30,239 --> 04:15:32,260
And then from there, the tears start coming.

2809
04:15:32,280 --> 04:15:35,862
Because I went back to when I was in my younger age, 13.

2810
04:15:37,323 --> 04:15:38,684
I went back to that age.

2811
04:15:39,125 --> 04:15:44,188
And all I can remember was, it was that face that used to beat me up.

2812
04:15:45,200 --> 04:15:47,841
The phase that I suffer under, I didn't see any change.

2813
04:15:48,461 --> 04:15:51,522
Then I just break down, tears start coming, and that's it.

2814
04:15:52,042 --> 04:15:54,323
And then what did you do when you were staring at Ayik?

2815
04:15:55,163 --> 04:15:56,264
I was really shaking.

2816
04:15:57,204 --> 04:16:03,946
I was thinking, if I go and sit next to Ayik, I was not sure what reaction Ayik will have.

2817
04:16:04,706 --> 04:16:12,729
And in the beginning, to be honest, Ayik's reaction was not good either to me, because he was crying, upset.

2818
04:16:13,383 --> 04:16:16,606
I was even scared that Ayik can do something to me.

2819
04:16:17,446 --> 04:16:23,351
So that was a really hard time for me to sit with Ayik and look face to face.

2820
04:16:24,351 --> 04:16:26,933
That was really a scary moment for me.

2821
04:16:27,053 --> 04:16:28,114
So you were afraid of him?

2822
04:16:28,775 --> 04:16:29,015
Yes.

2823
04:16:29,695 --> 04:16:31,577
Were you sorry for what you had done to him?

2824
04:16:32,197 --> 04:16:35,800
I was sorry, but I didn't did it intention to Ayik.

2825
04:16:36,631 --> 04:16:40,354
That's the order given to me, and I have to implement the order.

2826
04:16:40,654 --> 04:16:42,015
Did you have to be so cruel?

2827
04:16:42,656 --> 04:16:51,002
All I say, if my big boss told me, Nyang, your soldiers have to do this, I have to make sure that they done what I was told.

2828
04:16:51,562 --> 04:16:57,407
And you didn't have any doubts about the kind of pain, torture you were inflicting on those boys?

2829
04:16:58,027 --> 04:17:01,410
To be honest to you, I asked for the forgiveness.

2830
04:17:02,070 --> 04:17:05,813
And I told him that what I did, I knew is wrong.

2831
04:17:06,808 --> 04:17:09,269
But I was having a big boss ahead of me.

2832
04:17:10,329 --> 04:17:16,592
When you heard that from Anyang, when he said, look, you know, I had a boss who was giving me orders, how did you respond to that?

2833
04:17:17,252 --> 04:17:19,093
I think maybe he had his own problem.

2834
04:17:19,213 --> 04:17:20,213
I really don't understand.

2835
04:17:20,233 --> 04:17:29,177
You know, I realize now he's a good person, but there is something that I think that down the track Anyang needs to look into.

2836
04:17:29,437 --> 04:17:32,498
Treatment, because he's never been treated with anything at all.

2837
04:17:33,128 --> 04:17:39,995
It's clear that there are still many issues between you and yet, Ayik, you said, I realise he is a good person.

2838
04:17:40,676 --> 04:17:41,557
Where has that come from?

2839
04:17:41,577 --> 04:17:42,998
I forgive him.

2840
04:17:43,058 --> 04:17:45,721
I forgive him because he's got two grandkids.

2841
04:17:46,342 --> 04:17:47,523
I have one little boy.

2842
04:17:48,420 --> 04:17:50,701
And I know how much I love my little boy now.

2843
04:17:50,821 --> 04:17:52,302
So I just think the same with Anyang.

2844
04:17:52,362 --> 04:17:55,423
I know how much he loves his kids, how much he loves his grandkids.

2845
04:17:56,203 --> 04:18:00,685
And if I hold all the grudges for the rest of my life, it's me hurting myself.

2846
04:18:01,186 --> 04:18:04,747
Because everywhere I'm going to go here in Brisbane, I'm going to see him and I get angry.

2847
04:18:05,067 --> 04:18:07,808
That means that I'm the one hurting myself every time.

2848
04:18:08,289 --> 04:18:09,209
That's why I forgive him.

2849
04:18:10,009 --> 04:18:13,351
And after I've forgiven him, you know, we become good friends.

2850
04:18:14,283 --> 04:18:15,504
I go to his house now.

2851
04:18:15,524 --> 04:18:17,026
I sleep there.

2852
04:18:17,366 --> 04:18:19,268
Every time I go to his house, there's no spare bed.

2853
04:18:19,328 --> 04:18:20,469
I try to sleep on the couch.

2854
04:18:20,489 --> 04:18:22,210
He says, no, you sleep in the bed.

2855
04:18:22,230 --> 04:18:24,312
I say, all right, I'll sleep in the bed.

2856
04:18:24,693 --> 04:18:25,553
They'll give me food.

2857
04:18:25,613 --> 04:18:26,454
They give me anything.

2858
04:18:26,634 --> 04:18:30,058
If I get into any problem now, I think Anyang will stand up for me, I swear to God.

2859
04:18:30,138 --> 04:18:31,939
And if he get in trouble, I'll stand up for him.

2860
04:18:32,360 --> 04:18:39,586
Do you think that there is somehow a special bond between you, an element of your friendship which is rooted in this

2861
04:18:40,627 --> 04:18:42,709
shared experience you had all those years ago?

2862
04:18:43,069 --> 04:18:51,035
Yeah, that's the only one I can relate to in a way that this guy understands me as a child because my own family don't even know me.

2863
04:18:54,138 --> 04:19:00,542
It's because... Sorry.

2864
04:19:01,103 --> 04:19:04,125
Honestly, I've got the best family in the whole world.

2865
04:19:04,165 --> 04:19:07,328
My family will look after you before they look after me.

2866
04:19:07,488 --> 04:19:10,190
Not because they don't love me, that's how much they care.

2867
04:19:11,687 --> 04:19:13,068
They're a very caring family.

2868
04:19:13,469 --> 04:19:14,269
They're better than me.

2869
04:19:16,151 --> 04:19:17,352
All of them are better than me.

2870
04:19:18,633 --> 04:19:22,035
But the thing is, the bad thing is, I don't have a bond with them.

2871
04:19:22,776 --> 04:19:25,538
I can go to my mum's house now, just stay there.

2872
04:19:26,499 --> 04:19:28,520
After an hour, I want to get out of the house.

2873
04:19:29,161 --> 04:19:35,806
Not because I don't love them, but something just takes me out.

2874
04:19:36,627 --> 04:19:38,968
There's no bond because I grew away from them.

2875
04:19:39,569 --> 04:19:40,950
The best moment of my life.

2876
04:19:41,584 --> 04:19:42,745
that I should have spent with them.

2877
04:19:43,786 --> 04:19:45,067
I spent it in the rebel.

2878
04:19:47,208 --> 04:19:48,910
That's the only sad thing about this.

2879
04:19:49,330 --> 04:19:52,112
But apart from that, I forgive Anyang.

2880
04:19:53,533 --> 04:19:55,955
And I have so much to achieve, you know.

2881
04:19:55,975 --> 04:19:59,978
I want to just move on and try to build a bond with my family now.

2882
04:20:00,358 --> 04:20:01,219
That's the next one.

2883
04:20:01,679 --> 04:20:05,302
You have a son now, and you can be there with him.

2884
04:20:05,422 --> 04:20:06,843
You can be a father to him.

2885
04:20:07,970 --> 04:20:10,252
Yeah, I have my son's name Freeman.

2886
04:20:10,672 --> 04:20:11,073
Freeman?

2887
04:20:11,813 --> 04:20:15,436
Yeah, Freeman, like just Freeman, like a free man, you know, that's when he was born.

2888
04:20:15,496 --> 04:20:21,721
I thought, okay, I talked to his mama, said, I think the only name will make me happy after what I went through.

2889
04:20:21,901 --> 04:20:24,684
And I think Freeman is a free man.

2890
04:20:24,724 --> 04:20:27,106
And I'm a free man now, because I'm in a free country.

2891
04:20:27,326 --> 04:20:28,487
So I named him Freeman.

2892
04:20:29,548 --> 04:20:31,089
And he's one of the best kid I know.

2893
04:20:31,309 --> 04:20:31,830
How old is he?

2894
04:20:32,170 --> 04:20:32,330
He's 11.

2895
04:20:33,891 --> 04:20:34,632
What kind of boy is he?

2896
04:20:36,007 --> 04:20:39,930
Oh, he's a funny boy, you know, he's got that sense of humor, you know.

2897
04:20:39,970 --> 04:20:50,018
For example, sometime when I pick him up, we're driving down the street, and then I stop at the light, and I saw this one day we're driving, and there's these two girls looking at us.

2898
04:20:50,458 --> 04:20:52,440
I said, Freeman, look at them girls, they're checking me out.

2899
04:20:52,940 --> 04:20:56,163
And he said, Dad, because you're ugly.

2900
04:20:56,963 --> 04:20:57,523
You know what I mean?

2901
04:20:57,563 --> 04:20:58,664
All these little things.

2902
04:20:59,184 --> 04:21:01,084
I say no for him because I'm good looking.

2903
04:21:01,324 --> 04:21:03,325
I tell him if I was ugly, your mum wouldn't pick me.

2904
04:21:03,525 --> 04:21:05,205
So he's got that humour, you know?

2905
04:21:05,225 --> 04:21:06,245
He makes me laugh.

2906
04:21:06,266 --> 04:21:08,926
Ayik and Anyang meet up often now.

2907
04:21:08,986 --> 04:21:12,347
They talk about their past and they started writing a book together.

2908
04:21:12,747 --> 04:21:14,128
It means a lot to Anyang.

2909
04:21:14,668 --> 04:21:19,149
Now I'm working hard to build a good relationship between me and Ayik.

2910
04:21:20,306 --> 04:21:29,870
Because I ignored what I did, and he's the one who forgave me, so it's now my turn to do something to convince him that I was not that bad.

2911
04:21:30,550 --> 04:21:32,711
And what did you do to convince him that you're not that bad?

2912
04:21:32,731 --> 04:21:36,012
Yeah, like I have to talk with him every single day.

2913
04:21:36,753 --> 04:21:42,875
I have to come and see his child, and he does come and see my kid too.

2914
04:21:44,104 --> 04:21:50,488
So, and we just discuss the life, what should we achieve in the life ahead of us.

2915
04:21:50,869 --> 04:21:53,190
I wish we didn't go through what we went through.

2916
04:21:53,210 --> 04:21:55,652
I wish we started on a good foot.

2917
04:21:55,852 --> 04:22:00,836
It would have been better, but my world number one enemy become a good friend to me now.

2918
04:22:01,316 --> 04:22:02,497
I think the ending

2919
04:22:03,609 --> 04:22:05,470
It's really good.

