2924
04:22:36,915 --> 04:22:42,199
Now up in the highest mountains of Bhutan, there's an underground fungus that's very rare and very valuable.

2925
04:22:42,660 --> 04:22:47,343
Cordyceps are a group of parasitic fungi that grow mainly on the bodies of insects.

2926
04:22:47,704 --> 04:22:52,828
Some of them are worth twice their weight in gold, and people sometimes risk their lives to find them.

2927
04:22:53,528 --> 04:22:59,733
Not everyone going foraging is doing so legally, but Outlook's Canada Beverage has been to meet someone who is above board.

2928
04:23:00,294 --> 04:23:01,034
He's called Chawton.

2929
04:23:07,523 --> 04:23:13,307
Chawton lives in Nashville, a tiny, picturesque village in Bumthang Valley in central Bhutan.

2930
04:23:13,987 --> 04:23:18,510
It's as remote a place as you can imagine, with towering mountains all around.

2931
04:23:23,114 --> 04:23:28,737
He and his family have just returned from a month's camping, up where the snow line starts and the air is thin.

2932
04:23:29,378 --> 04:23:34,381
He's been collecting this year's harvest of cordyceps and invites me to join him for lunch.

2933
04:23:36,906 --> 04:23:44,300
taking our shoes off and going up some large wooden steps hello nice to meet you

2934
04:23:46,348 --> 04:23:48,470
So everyone's cooking.

2935
04:23:48,750 --> 04:23:49,550
Local dish, ma'am.

2936
04:23:49,750 --> 04:23:50,211
Local dish.

2937
04:23:50,231 --> 04:23:50,771
What is it?

2938
04:23:50,851 --> 04:23:51,712
Flat noodles.

2939
04:23:52,412 --> 04:23:53,073
Flat noodles.

2940
04:23:53,153 --> 04:23:54,173
Oh, they look delicious.

2941
04:23:54,233 --> 04:23:55,374
Is that what we're having for lunch?

2942
04:23:55,794 --> 04:23:57,195
Yes.

2943
04:23:57,335 --> 04:24:01,278
Chorten's daughter and wife bring out an incredible array of sumptuous food.

2944
04:24:01,298 --> 04:24:06,982
A meal like this would once have been impossible for this family, says Chorten.

2945
04:24:07,542 --> 04:24:09,984
That was until he discovered cordyceps.

2946
04:24:13,387 --> 04:24:20,656
When I was young and herding cattle, I knew about codices, but I didn't realize them, that they were so valuable.

2947
04:24:21,677 --> 04:24:25,561
The demand for them was started by the Chinese, who used them medicinally.

2948
04:24:26,462 --> 04:24:30,983
Cordyceps grow in the fertile high plateaus and mountains of Tibet and Bhutan.

2949
04:24:31,643 --> 04:24:33,704
They're antioxidant and antiviral.

2950
04:24:34,124 --> 04:24:41,906
It's for this reason and their scarcity that they fetch such high sums of money, sometimes priced at twice their weight in gold.

2951
04:24:43,706 --> 04:24:45,427
We've got some cordyceps in front of us.

2952
04:24:45,667 --> 04:24:46,867
They're very strange looking.

2953
04:24:46,927 --> 04:24:52,109
It's sort of like a caterpillar with a long strangled root coming out of it.

2954
04:24:53,629 --> 04:24:57,192
The odd appearance of the cordyceps is due to its unique nature.

2955
04:24:58,152 --> 04:25:03,877
It starts life as an underground dwelling caterpillar that becomes infected by a parasitic fungus.

2956
04:25:04,717 --> 04:25:09,601
The fungus engulfs the body of the caterpillar, leaving only its exoskeleton intact.

2957
04:25:10,161 --> 04:25:16,346
Then, at the start of spring, the fungus explodes through the caterpillar's head, poking a stalk up through the grass.

2958
04:25:19,909 --> 04:25:24,412
By looking at the top of the fungus, I can tell whether or not it is cordyceps.

2959
04:25:24,653 --> 04:25:28,875
It has a thing that looks like a black blade of grass poking out of the soil.

2960
04:25:29,876 --> 04:25:35,680
You have to be very close to the ground and be on your hands and knees with your face about a foot from the ground.

2961
04:25:36,561 --> 04:25:38,262
They are very difficult to spot.

2962
04:25:38,762 --> 04:25:44,526
I remember the first one I found, I was so happy because I was thinking how much money I would get.

2963
04:25:45,507 --> 04:25:46,988
They literally are like gold.

2964
04:25:47,008 --> 04:25:50,189
But nowadays, I don't think so much about the money.

2965
04:25:50,629 --> 04:25:55,650
I just feel immense happiness just to see one cordyceps because they are precious to me.

2966
04:25:56,311 --> 04:26:01,772
Searching for cordyceps takes place from early May until late June, up where the snow line starts.

2967
04:26:02,333 --> 04:26:05,454
Chawton shows me the track he takes up to the mountain pass.

2968
04:26:05,994 --> 04:26:06,814
Wow, look at that.

2969
04:26:06,874 --> 04:26:07,734
That's so steep.

2970
04:26:07,794 --> 04:26:12,316
How long does it take you to get up to where we can see just the top of the mountain?

2971
04:26:13,317 --> 04:26:18,881
To reach the summit where the snow line is, it takes three nights and four days.

2972
04:26:19,522 --> 04:26:28,469
I pack enough food to eat and drink, and a raincoat and heavy woolen clothes to protect against the cold if it snows.

2973
04:26:29,770 --> 04:26:32,032
We also need a tent and a sleeping bag.

2974
04:26:33,277 --> 04:26:34,498
We have to take horses.

2975
04:26:35,339 --> 04:26:39,603
When we camp, it can be hard to get wood for the fire and to pitch our tent.

2976
04:26:40,264 --> 04:26:42,546
Sometimes I'll be going with 20 people.

2977
04:26:43,286 --> 04:26:46,209
Sometimes it can be as many as 200 to 300 people.

2978
04:26:46,489 --> 04:26:48,932
Looking for cordyceps is not an easy task.

2979
04:26:49,452 --> 04:26:56,654
The altitude and vertiginous terrain means even the most experienced locals may lose their lives, and many do.

2980
04:26:57,314 --> 04:27:04,377
Once Chawton has collected all his cordyceps, he brings them down the mountain and waits for the auction date to be set, when he can sell them.

2981
04:27:05,037 --> 04:27:15,060
When he first started selling them, he was making around US$4,000 a year, but in recent years his profits have been far less because the fungus is getting harder to find.

2982
04:27:15,800 --> 04:27:18,621
This year's crop was even smaller than usual.

2983
04:27:22,522 --> 04:27:25,025
This must be around 130 grams.

2984
04:27:25,386 --> 04:27:28,330
This would be worth around 1000 US dollars.

2985
04:27:28,470 --> 04:27:31,153
And how has it changed your life, finding these cordyceps?

2986
04:27:31,433 --> 04:27:38,843
I paid for my house, the car parked outside, the TV, and the education of my children with money from cordyceps.

2987
04:27:39,734 --> 04:27:43,516
It has improved everybody's living standard so much.

2988
04:27:43,836 --> 04:27:47,037
We have everything we need because of this amazing fungus.

2989
04:27:48,077 --> 04:27:57,621
I'm hopeful that I'll be able to continue for the next five years, and then I'm not sure whether my body will endure the challenges of walking up to the mountains.

2990
04:27:58,081 --> 04:28:00,562
If my children are going to carry on, it is good.

2991
04:28:01,203 --> 04:28:03,544
If not, I guess that will be the end of cordyceps.

2992
04:28:04,204 --> 04:28:06,665
Chawton, speaking to Outlook's Canada Beverage.

