04:34:11,288 --> 04:34:16,992
But from that point on, we kind of knew that within the family, we have different opinions.

3063
04:34:17,812 --> 04:34:24,156
Our relations were based on Vitaly's loyalty.

3064
04:34:24,216 --> 04:34:26,078
He really didn't want to divorce.

3065
04:34:26,178 --> 04:34:28,019
He really wanted to save our marriage.

3066
04:34:28,619 --> 04:34:29,520
It was difficult.

3067
04:34:29,620 --> 04:34:37,347
This part of the relationship was really difficult, and both of us still don't understand how we were able to get through those years without getting divorced.

3068
04:34:37,827 --> 04:34:41,891
All the while Vitaly was struggling with what to do with the information Yulia had given him.

3069
04:34:42,051 --> 04:34:47,976
He had some contacts at the World Anti-Daping Agency, WADA, and was considering becoming a whistleblower.

3070
04:34:48,456 --> 04:34:50,978
I had to make up my own mind, what do I do?

3071
04:34:52,239 --> 04:34:59,285
Do I go against, I guess you can say against even my own home country and do I share the information with WADA?

3072
04:34:59,966 --> 04:35:12,857
And in the end I was invited to Vancouver to the Olympic Games and I spoke to one of the persons from WADA and I said I'm concerned about some things that I'm seeing and I think I should share it with you.

3073
04:35:14,158 --> 04:35:16,219
From that moment on I started telling

3074
04:35:17,412 --> 04:35:20,054
to my point of context, at what I was seeing.

3075
04:35:20,074 --> 04:35:27,921
I have to tell how I know things, and yeah, I said that my wife is involved in it as well, and I'm not sure what to do about it.

3076
04:35:28,021 --> 04:35:31,603
I mean, that's completely against the code, but this is the Russian reality.

3077
04:35:32,304 --> 04:35:38,789
Ever since I came back from Vancouver, I openly started to complain about the things that Rosada was not doing correctly.

3078
04:35:39,770 --> 04:35:45,655
Obviously, my bosses did not like that, and at some point, they openly started to try to get rid of me.

3079
04:35:46,547 --> 04:35:51,676
And finally, in February 2011, there was a reorganization, restructure.

3080
04:35:52,718 --> 04:35:57,487
It was kind of expected that I will not be kept in the newly restructured organization.

3081
04:35:58,343 --> 04:36:05,953
After Vitaly lost his job in February 2013, Yulia failed a drugs test and was banned from competing for two years.

3082
04:36:06,414 --> 04:36:16,747
It turned out that Yulia is going to become a scapegoat, even though the officials in Russia were saying that if you follow the system, you will never be sanctioned and we'll protect you.

3083
04:36:18,375 --> 04:36:24,779
But then it turned out that it's just not true.

3084
04:36:24,799 --> 04:36:28,422
Disqualification changed everything.

3085
04:36:29,302 --> 04:36:31,063
It actually saved our marriage.

3086
04:36:31,724 --> 04:36:35,406
Because after I was disqualified, I had three choices.

3087
04:36:35,686 --> 04:36:44,052
First, to continue and to keep silent and to continue taking drugs and be a part of this existing system.

3088
04:36:44,853 --> 04:36:51,361
The second choice was just to end up my career and just leave this big sport.

3089
04:36:51,841 --> 04:36:58,730
And the third one was actually to tell the truth to everyone about what's happening in the Russian sport with the doping.

3090
04:36:59,852 --> 04:37:08,935
I've decided to choose a third way to tell the truth and actually to find the system.

3091
04:37:09,155 --> 04:37:23,740
We've decided that our marriage is the main thing and we should be together, we should fight together all this illegal stuff and I had enough

3092
04:37:25,160 --> 04:37:28,141
strength to see the world in real terms.

3093
04:37:29,002 --> 04:37:31,062
So, for our family it was a blessing.

3094
04:37:31,082 --> 04:37:32,423
This crisis was a blessing.

3095
04:37:32,923 --> 04:37:42,887
Yulia started making secret recordings of her meetings with people involved in Russian doping.

3096
04:37:42,987 --> 04:37:47,409
The couple then approached a German investigative journalist, Hajo Seppelt, with their evidence.

3097
04:37:48,009 --> 04:37:52,751
They agreed to take part in a documentary which was to be aired on German television.

3098
04:37:53,251 --> 04:37:55,812
We could never imagine that we would actually go public with it.

3099
04:37:56,832 --> 04:38:04,856
It was in the beginning of 2014, more than a year after officially Yulei was providing statements, providing audio recordings.

3100
04:38:06,436 --> 04:38:14,540
We met Hajo Zeppelt, and we spoke to him, and he was actually the one who said, we got to try to fight this.

3101
04:38:15,220 --> 04:38:17,261
The more evidence we have, the better it would be.

3102
04:38:18,141 --> 04:38:20,482
Unfortunately, you know, as a journalist, he cannot

3103
04:38:21,670 --> 04:38:23,231
help us with getting the evidence.

3104
04:38:24,212 --> 04:38:36,980
So Julia was just talking to different athletes, coaches, and officials, just having normal conversations, only the difference was she always had her phone voice recording program on all the time.

3105
04:38:37,701 --> 04:38:40,383
We left the country, Russia, right before the documentary.

3106
04:38:40,723 --> 04:38:50,690
We knew that the reaction will be negative because protecting at least systematic doping in Russia, it's called being a patriot in Russia.

3107
04:38:51,801 --> 04:38:59,747
And even though I do not share this point of view, I could understand that as soon as this information is out, we will be called traitors and liars.

3108
04:39:00,508 --> 04:39:02,069
And that's exactly what happened.

3109
04:39:02,349 --> 04:39:07,013
So I had to make sure that we go public, but that our family feels safe.

3110
04:39:07,133 --> 04:39:09,775
And I knew that we wouldn't feel safe in Russia.

3111
04:39:10,580 --> 04:39:15,166
Yulia and Vitaly watched the story break from their temporary home in Germany.

3112
04:39:15,687 --> 04:39:21,715
Soon the World Anti-Doping Agency commissioned an independent commission to investigate the claims made in that documentary.

3113
04:39:21,895 --> 04:39:26,301
The report confirmed the existence of widespread cheating in Russia through doping.

3114
04:39:27,202 --> 04:39:36,428
The aftermath has been bittersweet for the couple, as Yulia has since been banned from competing at the Rio Olympics because of her own doping charge in 2013.

3115
04:39:40,931 --> 04:39:43,933
I don't want to whitewash my own past.

3116
04:39:44,013 --> 04:39:52,599
Obviously, I know what I did was wrong, and I want to apologize before all the clean athletes for what I did.

3117
04:39:53,319 --> 04:39:54,119
But you know what?

3118
04:39:54,460 --> 04:39:55,781
I cannot change my past.

3119
04:39:56,601 --> 04:40:08,612
The only thing I can do is actually try to change the current situation and the future and to be just another person.

3120
04:40:08,972 --> 04:40:16,659
Right from the beginning, I understood that, unfortunately, the best supporters in doping fighting are investigative journalists.

3121
04:40:18,153 --> 04:40:24,075
If a journalist approaches us and wants to talk to us and wants to hear us, we will tell our story.

3122
04:40:25,036 --> 04:40:29,518
It's not a pretty story, but it's a real story and we are telling the truth.

3123
04:40:29,578 --> 04:40:37,461
We will keep apologizing for our own mistakes and we are trying to change and at least as a family I am sure that we are doing a good job.

3124
04:40:38,221 --> 04:40:42,943
A new relationship is not easy to build, but we are working on it and it's improving.

3125
04:40:44,030 --> 04:40:47,132
We have a two-year-old son, and we try to be good parents now.

3126
04:40:50,134 --> 04:40:54,677
Even I was banned from the Rio Olympic Games.

3127
04:40:55,358 --> 04:41:02,662
I think that we made the right choice, because it didn't affect our marriage, it didn't affect our relations.

3128
04:41:06,317 --> 04:41:09,620
young athletes will help sport in future.

3129
04:41:09,640 --> 04:41:12,922
Yulia and Vitaly Stepanov speaking in 2016.

3130
04:41:12,962 --> 04:41:13,803
They're still in hiding.

3131
04:41:21,268 --> 04:41:29,833
Now, we're off to the north of Italy, to the valleys around the city of Genoa, where a herd of cattle has been making the headlines after running away from their owner.

3132
04:41:29,853 --> 04:41:32,335
They've been dubbed the rebel cows.

3133
04:41:33,015 --> 04:41:39,940
Let's get the story from local scientist and documentary maker Alessandro Ghigi, who's been following the rebel cows deep into the woods.

3134
04:41:40,320 --> 04:41:41,921
It's a territory he knows well.

3135
04:41:42,741 --> 04:41:50,845
I grew up in a city, but I've always been passionate about science and nature.

3136
04:41:51,446 --> 04:41:55,088
My dad is a hunter and we would always go hiking in the countryside.

3137
04:41:55,548 --> 04:41:59,570
He would be killing animals, while I was more interested in taking pictures of them.

3138
04:42:00,630 --> 04:42:03,192
I soon became a keen bird watcher.

3139
04:42:03,732 --> 04:42:09,375
I got used to hide in the bushes, completely still, waiting for hours for a bird to approach.

3140
04:42:12,458 --> 04:42:17,640
Throughout the years, I became very familiar with the mountains and woods surrounding Genoa.

3141
04:42:18,000 --> 04:42:21,961
It's a very harsh place, with narrow valleys and steep slopes.

3142
04:42:22,741 --> 04:42:24,442
It's also a wild place.

3143
04:42:24,602 --> 04:42:27,303
Wolves and wild boars inhabit these forests.

3144
04:42:30,593 --> 04:42:34,499
I normally go hiking there with some friends looking for wild animals to photograph.

3145
04:42:35,039 --> 04:42:38,985
One day we heard a story from a local that caught our attention.

3146
04:42:39,506 --> 04:42:41,989
It's the story of the rebel cows.

3147
04:42:50,504 --> 04:42:53,709
The rebel cows are a mysterious presence in these valleys.

3148
04:42:54,149 --> 04:42:57,334
It's a herd that has been living in the wild for almost seven years.

3149
04:42:57,974 --> 04:43:02,441
They're a very elusive bunch and they're surrounded by an aura of mystery.

3150
04:43:03,142 --> 04:43:06,286
Everybody who lives in the villages up here has a story to tell about them.

3151
04:43:08,507 --> 04:43:14,510
This group of cows must have had something special to begin with, to be able to break free in the way they did.

3152
04:43:14,530 --> 04:43:16,091
It's just unbelievable.

3153
04:43:16,551 --> 04:43:19,713
I don't know much about how they managed to escape in the first place.

3154
04:43:20,393 --> 04:43:21,294
It must have been around 2010.

3155
04:43:22,915 --> 04:43:25,596
People told us that they belonged to a local farmer.

3156
04:43:25,856 --> 04:43:28,597
They had been sold and they had to be driven away.

3157
04:43:29,258 --> 04:43:37,102
But as the farmer was trying to get them into a lorry, a small group of them broke free and they simply disappeared in the bushes.

3158
04:43:38,240 --> 04:43:41,221
Since then, the rebel cows have been living in the woods.

3159
04:43:57,847 --> 04:44:00,888
Local authorities tried everything they could to catch them.

3160
04:44:01,595 --> 04:44:05,017
They even brought in expert cowboys, but nothing worked.

3161
04:44:05,878 --> 04:44:10,820
And because of the nature of these wild valleys, it's incredibly difficult to build traps.

3162
04:44:11,301 --> 04:44:17,004
The rebel cows are still at large.

3163
04:44:17,044 --> 04:44:23,127
My friends and I were immediately captivated by the story of the rebel cows and by their indomitable spirit.

3164
04:44:23,327 --> 04:44:24,808
We don't know how big the herd is.

3165
04:44:25,249 --> 04:44:26,870
A few years ago, it was of about 15.

3166
04:44:28,387 --> 04:44:31,429
We know there's a bull among them, and calves have been born.

3167
04:44:32,250 --> 04:44:37,013
But throughout the years, the herd was decimated by diseases and natural deaths.

3168
04:44:37,653 --> 04:44:44,378
Some of them have been found dead in ditches, horribly wounded, because, unfortunately, poachers are operating in the area.

3169
04:44:45,062 --> 04:44:46,802
and they are looking for the cows too.

3170
04:44:47,383 --> 04:44:49,663
Now we think there are only six cows left.

3171
04:44:54,104 --> 04:44:58,265
But I mean, you have to give them credit.

3172
04:44:58,305 --> 04:45:04,746
The rebel cows have been living in the wild for seven years and survived several attempts of capturing or killing them.

3173
04:45:05,186 --> 04:45:06,347
It's a unique case.

3174
04:45:08,567 --> 04:45:12,348
The most interesting thing about the rebel cows is that their behavior changed.

3175
04:45:12,888 --> 04:45:14,851
They turned into a wild herd.

3176
04:45:18,054 --> 04:45:21,939
Because of their elusive attitude, it's almost impossible to study them.

3177
04:45:22,840 --> 04:45:27,124
So my friends and I decided to put together a little documentary about them.

3178
04:45:27,885 --> 04:45:33,271
We positioned several hidden cameras in the woods, in places where we thought they might roam around.

3179
04:45:35,911 --> 04:45:38,313
We didn't have to wait long to get our first footage.

3180
04:45:38,854 --> 04:45:43,398
One day, my friend Paolo went to collect the SD card from the camera, and he called me.

3181
04:45:43,679 --> 04:45:46,201
He was so excited, he screamed, we have the cows!

3182
04:45:46,782 --> 04:45:50,866
Oh, he was so happy.

3183
04:45:51,446 --> 04:45:56,231
I still remember seeing them appearing in the footage, walking around, then fleeing from something.

3184
04:45:58,597 --> 04:46:03,043
I'm sure you're all familiar with the video of a cow, and that's usually boring.

3185
04:46:03,483 --> 04:46:05,486
But this is nothing like that.

3186
04:46:06,006 --> 04:46:13,816
The footage is shot at night with an infrared camera, so the rebel cows look like extraordinary and mysterious creatures.

3187
04:46:18,108 --> 04:46:18,909
They're crossbred.

3188
04:46:19,410 --> 04:46:27,299
The females are light brown, almost gingerish, while the calves are darker, mainly black, and they behave like wild animals.

3189
04:46:27,840 --> 04:46:31,825
They hide in the forest during the day and only come out to graze at night.

3190
04:46:32,425 --> 04:46:34,468
They move in perfect silence.

3191
04:46:34,928 --> 04:46:43,072
Locals who saw them noticed that there is what we would call a sentinel in the group.

3192
04:46:43,633 --> 04:46:53,278
While the others eat, she stays on the side, her back to the group, nose in the air, sniffing the potential dangers, ready to tell the other cows to run and hide.

3193
04:46:53,978 --> 04:46:56,961
And from what we know, they are extremely agile.

3194
04:46:57,341 --> 04:47:04,546
They run and jump around like deer.

3195
04:47:04,586 --> 04:47:10,731
While filming our doc, we tried to remain impartial, but we're obviously biased because we cheer for the cows.

3196
04:47:11,352 --> 04:47:14,814
Of course, not everybody is excited as we are about the rebel cows.

3197
04:47:15,194 --> 04:47:19,618
The villages in these valleys are very small, and people rely mostly on agriculture.

3198
04:47:20,225 --> 04:47:25,169
During the winter, the rebel cows come down the mountains and they break into gardens and allotments.

3199
04:47:25,609 --> 04:47:34,877
You have to understand, these animals weigh 500 or 600 kilos, so if they spot a cabbage they are really interested in, be sure they will do everything they can to get it.

3200
04:47:35,617 --> 04:47:39,138
And that often means trampling down fences and damaging fields.

3201
04:47:41,559 --> 04:47:44,200
Lots of people around here would like to capture or kill them.

3202
04:47:44,700 --> 04:47:50,302
But some scientists would like to let them be, because it would be very interesting to do more research on them.

3203
04:47:50,882 --> 04:47:54,664
And our documentary created a lot of hype around the rebel cows.

3204
04:47:55,604 --> 04:47:58,345
They have become resistance icons in Italy.

3205
04:47:58,365 --> 04:48:09,346
People are fascinated by their rebel spirit, and that's what I love about them too.

3206
04:48:09,747 --> 04:48:20,308
When you think about the fact that these animals have been tamed thousands of years ago, and for all this time they have lived with humans, the idea that they can break free and run away is just extraordinary.

3207
04:48:20,988 --> 04:48:23,509
I never had a face-to-face encounter with one of them,

3208
04:48:24,189 --> 04:48:27,131
But in a way, this is what keeps my interest going.

3209
04:48:27,672 --> 04:48:29,893
It keeps the mystery intact.

3210
04:48:32,215 --> 04:48:33,316
Long live the cows.

3211
04:48:37,899 --> 04:48:41,982
Alessandro Ghigi on the trail of the rebel cows in northern Italy.

3212
04:48:42,923 --> 04:48:52,867
Now a witness, and today we're going back 50 years to 1967, the British withdrawal from the port city of Aden, and the creation of the People's Republic of South Yemen.

3213
04:48:53,287 --> 04:49:03,572
Farhana Haider has been speaking to a former British diplomat, Oliver Miles, who was instrumental in Britain's departure, and Tugarsun Lukman, who as a teenager lived through that time.

3214
04:49:04,752 --> 04:49:15,676
With torchlight processions and dancing in the streets, the people are celebrating independence, although they're still awaiting the arrival of the National Liberation Front leaders from Geneva.

3215
04:49:16,196 --> 04:49:22,478
Britain had colonised the port city of Aden in 1839, one of the longest inhabited places on earth.

3216
04:49:23,039 --> 04:49:32,482
The colony consisted of Aden and the British protectorates of South Arabia, desert hinterlands which surrounded the city, controlled by tribal leaders.

3217
04:49:33,182 --> 04:49:38,744
But by the 1950s, Britain's retreat from empire around the world was well underway.

3218
04:49:38,764 --> 04:49:43,046
And in the Middle East, there was a rising wave of Arab nationalism.

3219
04:49:46,748 --> 04:49:48,409
There were definitely celebrations.

3220
04:49:48,949 --> 04:49:50,950
It was a happy day for many people.

3221
04:49:50,970 --> 04:49:58,713
And for many others, it was a day of reflection of what happened in the past and what could have the effect on the future.

3222
04:49:59,465 --> 04:50:05,407
Ghazan Luqman was 14 years old in November 1967, and from a prominent Adeny family.

3223
04:50:05,967 --> 04:50:11,268
While he remembers jubilation on the day of independence, there was also a sense of uncertainty.

3224
04:50:11,288 --> 04:50:13,009
I think the mood was somber.

3225
04:50:13,309 --> 04:50:16,110
People were apprehensive as to what would come next.

3226
04:50:16,130 --> 04:50:17,170
Yes, exactly.

3227
04:50:17,530 --> 04:50:19,391
And their apprehension proved to be right.

3228
04:50:19,611 --> 04:50:22,591
It was good to see the colonial power was gone, but then what's next?

3229
04:50:23,192 --> 04:50:27,813
The people of Aden, I would say, probably the majority was very scared of the future.

3230
04:50:28,398 --> 04:50:31,443
Aden was at the centre of the British colonial trading system.

3231
04:50:31,823 --> 04:50:36,911
Ships stopped there to refuel en route between Europe and India, the Far East and Australia.

3232
04:50:37,311 --> 04:50:39,294
It was one of the busiest ports in the world.

3233
04:50:39,675 --> 04:50:43,641
Growing up in the city, Gazan Lukman remembers it being prosperous and modern.

3234
04:50:44,081 --> 04:50:47,123
As a teenager growing in Eden, life was good.

3235
04:50:47,324 --> 04:50:50,906
The majority of people were enjoying their progress at that time.

3236
04:50:51,147 --> 04:50:53,548
Electronics were available at that time.

3237
04:50:53,568 --> 04:50:56,831
Eden was actually a hub or a center because of tourism.

3238
04:50:57,051 --> 04:51:00,414
You could buy the best watches of the time, fancy clothing.

3239
04:51:00,754 --> 04:51:05,678
The big passenger ships bring swarms of tourists to the famous duty-free crescent of shops ashore.

3240
04:51:05,938 --> 04:51:13,620
Life was good, and it was a paradise lost from textile to perfumes to consumer goods.

3241
04:51:13,940 --> 04:51:16,061
Aden had great beaches.

3242
04:51:16,661 --> 04:51:19,882
Aden had great airport, great port.

3243
04:51:20,282 --> 04:51:23,022
Aden was the Dubai of the 1960s.

3244
04:51:23,623 --> 04:51:25,083
It was a liberal city.

3245
04:51:25,463 --> 04:51:33,508
There was, however, growing resentment at the British presence, and although they had announced they were withdrawing from Aden, they hadn't fixed the date.

3246
04:51:33,928 --> 04:51:38,350
We've said we'll quit by 1968, yet the terrorist attacks become more frequent.

3247
04:51:38,691 --> 04:51:40,652
We can't be allowed to just pack up and go.

3248
04:51:41,092 --> 04:51:48,395
Oliver Miles was posted to Yemen in 1966 and appointed private secretary to the British High Commissioner in Aden.

3249
04:51:48,595 --> 04:51:56,679
And as private secretary, of course, I was in a position of absolutely in the centre of everything that happened in the last six, nine months before independence.

3250
04:51:57,079 --> 04:51:59,760
And by 1967, there was growing violence.

3251
04:52:00,100 --> 04:52:04,082
Two armed movements were vying to lead a new post-independent government.

3252
04:52:04,482 --> 04:52:11,925
FLOSSI, the Front for the Liberation of South Yemen, who was supported by Egypt, and the NLF, a Marxist movement.

3253
04:52:12,165 --> 04:52:20,629
The people who were fighting us, we called them terrorists, the Front for the Liberation of South Yemen and the National Liberation Front, the two rival groups.

3254
04:52:21,329 --> 04:52:27,077
They didn't really believe that they were going to go because they thought that Aden was too important to the British Empire and there was no way we were going to go.

3255
04:52:27,158 --> 04:52:37,251
So although the first of those two groups, the Front for Liberation of South Yemen, was moderately prepared to see themselves as a future government and therefore be ready to talk to us about the process,

3256
04:52:37,952 --> 04:52:40,874
the National Liberation Front were absolutely not willing to talk to us.

3257
04:52:41,254 --> 04:52:51,480
And as the time of independence drew closer, the two fought each other, literally fought each other in the streets with a good deal of bloodshed, and the NLF won.

3258
04:52:51,641 --> 04:53:01,727
This is the flag of the terrorists of Aden, the red, white and black tricolour of the National Liberation Front, a symbol of the NLF's triumph over its rivals Flossie.

3259
04:53:01,847 --> 04:53:05,529
Events leading to independence were not great.

3260
04:53:05,809 --> 04:53:06,690
There was a civil war.

3261
04:53:07,050 --> 04:53:10,733
Do you remember feeling scared because of the war happening around you?

3262
04:53:11,174 --> 04:53:20,562
Very scared, especially during night time, because if you are perceived to be from the other group, the other group will come and drag you in the middle of the night, and many people disappear.

3263
04:53:20,983 --> 04:53:22,124
One of them was my brother.

3264
04:53:22,904 --> 04:53:26,267
And so we were very, very scared.

3265
04:53:26,467 --> 04:53:29,030
To actually see a civil war was very sad.

3266
04:53:29,450 --> 04:53:34,712
Having won the civil war, the NLF now sat down for talks with the British to negotiate the withdrawal.

3267
04:53:34,972 --> 04:53:42,215
Geneva and the lakeside setting for the first political confrontation between the terrorists of Aden and the British government.

3268
04:53:42,415 --> 04:53:49,718
It became clear in the last month or so before independence that we were going to hand over to people we'd never met, literally never met.

3269
04:53:50,158 --> 04:53:53,700
In that building over there, that Britain will meet the National Liberation Front

3270
04:53:54,541 --> 04:54:07,572
To our surprise, we found one or two faces on the other side of the table were familiar, but they were familiar in different guises, if you like, because there was one senior police officer from the Aden police who we thought was on our side, but it turned out he was a senior NLF man.

3271
04:54:08,092 --> 04:54:14,298
There was an army officer, similarly, and at that time, of course, the British Empire was shedding its colonies like autumn leaves.

3272
04:54:14,898 --> 04:54:21,406
Normally, it's a long process where a lot of people spend a lot of time in each other's offices, getting to know how systems work.

3273
04:54:21,726 --> 04:54:26,592
But because the NLF were our enemy, we didn't have time to do that, and it was all done in a terrible rush.

3274
04:54:26,772 --> 04:54:31,517
I could see that my friends, the Adenese and the Yemenis, were in for a hell of a time after we left.

3275
04:54:31,698 --> 04:54:32,759
That was perfectly obvious.

3276
04:54:32,999 --> 04:54:46,892
If only because Aden City, Aden Town, was to some extent a creation of the British Empire, and the fact that the British were leaving, in particular the British military base was closing down, meant that they were losing half the source of their income.

3277
04:54:47,613 --> 04:54:53,839
And the other half they'd lost already because the Suez Canal had been closed following the 1967 war, so the trade was off.

3278
04:54:54,019 --> 04:54:55,641
So they were left with nothing to live on.

3279
04:54:56,321 --> 04:54:59,623
Aden was clearly going to nosedive as we left, we could see that.

3280
04:54:59,763 --> 04:55:09,948
The government was resorting to more and more repressive measures, but that was not immediately after amendments, that was when the situation deteriorated maybe a year later or two years later.

3281
04:55:10,329 --> 04:55:14,451
Do you feel that the British had let down the people of Aden?

3282
04:55:15,457 --> 04:55:16,819
I don't think that it was our fault.

3283
04:55:17,039 --> 04:55:19,401
I think we did the best we could in the circumstances.

3284
04:55:19,761 --> 04:55:31,012
You can argue that we let the people of Yemen or of South Yemen down more broadly, that they weren't ready for independence, that they didn't really want independence, most of them, many of them, and that we got out in a rush.

3285
04:55:31,632 --> 04:55:41,462
Britain left behind deep divisions between those who'd worked for the colonial government and those that had fought against it, and between supporters of the different independence movements.

3286
04:55:42,083 --> 04:55:49,430
Guzun Lukman found that many of his friends and family were targeted by the repressive and pro-Soviet state that later emerged.

3287
04:55:49,771 --> 04:55:50,772
He soon left Aden.

3288
04:55:51,962 --> 04:55:55,504
Many Adenese felt that they were betrayed by Britain, unfortunately.

3289
04:55:55,544 --> 04:56:01,227
The withdrawal from Aden was abrupt, it was fast, just gone, just overnight.

3290
04:56:01,447 --> 04:56:07,570
Families, people we knew in our neighbourhood, everybody was actually gone, just like a wolf.

3291
04:56:08,011 --> 04:56:12,153
Wake up and they're gone, which left many people apprehensive and bewildered.

3292
04:56:12,353 --> 04:56:15,835
When you think about independence now, do you think it was a good thing?

3293
04:56:16,315 --> 04:56:17,556
I think it was premature.

3294
04:56:17,776 --> 04:56:19,597
It should have taken maybe a few more years.

3295
04:56:19,997 --> 04:56:23,579
They should have brought everybody and put them around the same table.

3296
04:56:24,279 --> 04:56:28,542
In 1990, communist South Yemen merged with the separate state of North Yemen.

3297
04:56:28,882 --> 04:56:32,083
But the divisions within Yemeni society have never gone away.

3298
04:56:32,644 --> 04:56:38,327
And Ghazan believes Britain bears much of the responsibility for the violence that still blights the country.

3299
04:56:38,347 --> 04:56:40,388
The people of England have gone through a lot.

3300
04:56:41,388 --> 04:56:45,752
From 1967 up to now, the older generations went through a lot.

3301
04:56:46,753 --> 04:56:54,260
Many of them, they just wait for the day they die because it has been nothing but downhill changes since 1967, unfortunately.

3302
04:56:54,480 --> 04:57:00,886
Do you think the situation that Yemen is in now is partly as a result of the British leaving so quickly?

3303
04:57:01,326 --> 04:57:02,627
Yes, absolutely.

3304
04:57:03,587 --> 04:57:10,370
And I hope that Britain helps now in sorting the issue of the conflict between the North and the South.

3305
04:57:10,730 --> 04:57:14,552
It will be a sort of a make-up for what they, when they left in a hurry and a half.

3306
04:57:14,812 --> 04:57:18,634
I think Britain could actually, they should help them in resolving the conflict.

3307
04:57:18,994 --> 04:57:21,255
And do you miss your home city?

3308
04:57:21,616 --> 04:57:22,136
Extremely.

3309
04:57:22,776 --> 04:57:24,817
And the older you get, the more you miss it.

3310
04:57:24,957 --> 04:57:26,098
I miss my family.

3311
04:57:26,118 --> 04:57:28,279
I miss Eden very much.

3312
04:57:28,579 --> 04:57:30,520
I think of it every day of my life.

3313
04:57:31,449 --> 04:57:33,351
Guthen Luchmann now lives in Ottawa.

3314
04:57:33,891 --> 04:57:40,156
Oliver Mars retired from the diplomatic service in 1996 and is the editor of the Arab Digest.

3315
04:57:43,541 --> 04:57:45,482
And that report was by Fahana Haider.

3316
04:57:45,682 --> 04:57:47,003
That's all from Outlook for today.

3317
04:57:47,083 --> 04:57:48,704
Matthew will be here tomorrow.

3318
04:57:49,224 --> 04:57:54,487
He's hearing from a high-flying Kenyan banker who was jailed for a crime she didn't commit.

3319
04:57:55,087 --> 04:58:00,089
She will tell you, Matthew, what she learned in prison and how she fought to clear her name.

3320
04:58:00,269 --> 04:58:02,551
Do join him for that same time tomorrow.

3321
04:58:03,071 --> 04:58:07,013
But for today, from me, Jo Fidgen, and the rest of the Outlook team, thanks for listening.

3322
04:58:08,485 --> 04:58:13,526
You're listening to the BBC World Service, and here's what's happening in the studio this week.

3323
04:58:15,026 --> 04:58:18,927
Meet Arnd Henning Hessen, one of the top mixologists in the world.

3324
04:58:19,447 --> 04:58:26,408
He captures smells and tastes from across the globe, from frankincense from Oman to tonka beans from Madagascar.

3325
04:58:26,868 --> 04:58:30,869
And who can create a drink for you based on just the perfume you're wearing.

3326
04:58:31,329 --> 04:58:35,870
In the studio at bbcworldservice.com slash inthestudio.

3327
04:58:39,207 --> 04:58:41,810
And in half an hour on Click with Gareth Mitchell.

3328
04:58:42,370 --> 04:58:49,677
Farmers in India are receiving advisories by text or voicemail telling them the best time to sow their crops.

3329
04:58:50,078 --> 04:58:55,423
The alerts come from data from sensors in the ground combined with historical climate records.

3330
04:58:56,264 --> 04:58:56,924
Stay with us.

3331
04:58:57,105 --> 04:59:01,369
The Newsroom is next on the BBC World Service, the world's radio station.

3332
04:59:08,898 --> 04:59:13,183
BBC World Service, it's five o'clock GMT, this is Oliver Conway with the Newsroom.

3333
04:59:13,604 --> 04:59:19,610
In a break with international consensus, Donald Trump is expected to declare Jerusalem to be capital of Israel.

3334
04:59:19,931 --> 04:59:23,435
I know there have been a lot of questions surrounding the President's decision on Jerusalem.

3335
04:59:23,895 --> 04:59:25,738
Tomorrow the President will deliver remarks.

3336
04:59:26,358 --> 04:59:27,939
Has the president made up his mind?

3337
04:59:28,439 --> 04:59:31,620
The president is pretty solid in his thinking at this point.

3338
04:59:32,060 --> 04:59:34,521
Arab leaders have warned of dangerous repercussions.

3339
04:59:35,041 --> 04:59:35,781
Also on the newsroom.

3340
04:59:36,121 --> 04:59:37,362
It's a political decision.

3341
04:59:37,522 --> 04:59:45,184
Very bad decision and I disagree with this position of the World Olympic Committee and so on.

3342
04:59:45,544 --> 04:59:49,046
Russia has reacted angrily after it was banned from the Winter Olympics.

3343
04:59:49,686 --> 04:59:53,367
We report from the Damascus suburb which has faced a relentless bombardment.

3344
04:59:55,128 --> 05:00:00,313
I wish I could have cookies, sweeties, or any other delicious foods.

3345
05:00:00,954 --> 05:00:02,015
I really miss food.

3346
05:00:02,696 --> 05:00:05,678
And France's biggest rock star, Johnny Hallyday, has died.

3347
05:00:06,079 --> 05:00:07,020
First, our top stories.

3348
05:00:08,680 --> 05:00:10,761
BBC News, hello, I'm Gareth Barlow.

3349
05:00:11,401 --> 05:00:12,202
Senior U.S.

3350
05:00:12,242 --> 05:00:17,564
officials say President Trump will recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel later on Wednesday.

3351
05:00:18,024 --> 05:00:23,987
He'll also direct the State Department to start the process of moving the American embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.

3352
05:00:24,647 --> 05:00:28,469
Arab states have warned that the decision could provoke violence in the Muslim world.

3353
05:00:28,989 --> 05:00:29,870
Peter Bowes reports.

3354
05:00:30,550 --> 05:00:33,852
Donald Trump is venturing into uncharted territory.

3355
05:00:34,252 --> 05:00:43,096
The president will recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel, making the US the first country to do so since the foundation of the state in 1948.

3356
05:00:44,216 --> 05:00:49,819
According to the White House press secretary Sarah Sanders, Mr Trump's thinking on the issue is pretty solid.

3357
05:00:50,536 --> 05:00:58,218
He's already indicated that he intends to move the American embassy to Jerusalem from Tel Aviv and has informed regional leaders of his plans.

3358
05:00:58,918 --> 05:01:00,458
The reaction has been heated.

3359
05:01:01,038 --> 05:01:09,140
The Palestinian leader, Mahmoud Abbas, has warned of dangerous consequences for the peace, security and stability of the region and of the world.

3360
05:01:09,780 --> 05:01:16,062
Jordan's King Abdullah said the decision would undermine efforts to resume the peace process and provoke Muslims.

3361
05:01:16,877 --> 05:01:24,581
Russia has reacted furiously to a decision by the International Olympic Committee to ban it from next February's Winter Olympics in South Korea.

3362
05:01:25,102 --> 05:01:31,865
A damning report by the IOC said there had been an unprecedented systematic manipulation of the anti-doping system.

3363
05:01:32,386 --> 05:01:34,307
From Moscow, here's Steve Rosenberg.

3364
05:01:35,007 --> 05:01:39,770
The deputy speaker of Russia's parliament said it was a humiliation and an insult to Russia.

3365
05:01:40,610 --> 05:01:52,279
In a defiant post in social media, the spokeswoman for the Russian Foreign Ministry said Russia would survive this like it survived World War, the collapse of the Soviet Union and Western sanctions.

3366
05:01:53,299 --> 05:02:02,646
Although the Russian team has been banned from competing in South Korea, Russian athletes who can prove they are clean will be permitted to participate under the Olympic flag.

3367
05:02:03,346 --> 05:02:05,088
But will the Kremlin allow them to?

3368
05:02:05,768 --> 05:02:11,011
Vladimir Putin has in the past described such a scenario as a humiliation for his country.

3369
05:02:11,352 --> 05:02:12,652
Steve Rosenberg reporting.

3370
05:02:13,253 --> 05:02:18,396
Tens of thousands of people in Southern California have fled wildfires being driven by high winds.

3371
05:02:18,936 --> 05:02:21,858
James Cook reports from the outskirts of Los Angeles.

3372
05:02:22,457 --> 05:02:34,680
In Ventura County, to the north of Los Angeles, a wildfire which broke out on Monday intensified with terrifying speed, trembling in size in just a few hours, driven by arid and gusty Santa Ana winds.

3373
05:02:35,200 --> 05:02:43,283
Here on the outskirts of Los Angeles, the charred ruins of houses are still smoking, while dark, choking smoke has closed a major moat away.

3374
05:02:43,823 --> 05:02:47,624
Ash is blowing through the air, and there is a firefighting helicopter overhead.

3375
05:02:48,670 --> 05:02:56,999
Three men in Malta have been charged with the murder of the anti-corruption journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia, who was killed by a car bomb in October.

3376
05:02:57,020 --> 05:03:01,605
Alfred and George DiGiorgio and Vince Muscat were arrested on Monday.

3377
05:03:01,985 --> 05:03:04,067
They have pleaded not guilty to the charges.

3378
05:03:04,908 --> 05:03:06,630
World News from the BBC.

3379
05:03:08,236 --> 05:03:15,501
A new report says about 15,000 people a day are being forced to flee their homes in African conflict and disaster zones.

3380
05:03:16,041 --> 05:03:20,124
Figures show that more than 12 million people in Africa are internally displaced.

3381
05:03:20,584 --> 05:03:22,746
Nearly 4 million left their homes last year.

3382
05:03:23,982 --> 05:03:31,329
Britain's most prestigious contemporary art award, the Turner Prize, has been won by an art professor who was born in Zanzibar, Labena Habib.

3383
05:03:31,910 --> 05:03:36,274
Judges praised her work, which explores the African diaspora and black creativity.

3384
05:03:36,674 --> 05:03:41,058
Professor Himid is the first black woman and the oldest person to win the award.

3385
05:03:42,454 --> 05:03:52,339
Scientists at Oxford University have carried out the first radiocarbon dating of a fragment of bone claimed to be from Saint Nicholas, believed to be the inspiration for Father Christmas.

3386
05:03:52,880 --> 05:03:58,463
Their findings revealed that the bone was 1,700 years old, matching the era of the saint's life.

3387
05:03:58,943 --> 05:04:00,244
Sean Coughlin has the story.

3388
05:04:00,884 --> 05:04:10,029
Relics of Saint Nicholas have been venerated in churches since at least the 11th century, and his popularity meant that hundreds of bones are claimed to have come from the Christmas saint.

3389
05:04:10,869 --> 05:04:21,498
This fragment of pelvis, tested at the University of Oxford, had come from a church in France, and Professor Tom Hyam said many such relics turn out to be not nearly as old as claimed.

3390
05:04:22,178 --> 05:04:29,964
But researchers were taken aback when test results showed that the bone really was from the era of Saint Nicholas, almost 1700 years ago.

3391
05:04:29,984 --> 05:04:37,630
Although there's no definite proof, Professor Hyam said it was possible that the remains could indeed be those of Saint Nicholas himself.

3392
05:04:38,651 --> 05:04:44,235
France's biggest rock star, Johnny Halliday, has died at the age of 74 after a battle with lung cancer.

3393
05:04:44,796 --> 05:04:50,860
In a career spanning five decades, he sold more than 100 million records and headlined 50 major tours.

3394
05:04:51,441 --> 05:04:58,226
Influenced by the music of Elvis Presley, Johnny Halliday began his career in 1960, singing rock and roll in French.

3395
05:04:58,806 --> 05:05:04,250
Known as the French Elvis, he was hugely popular in the Francophone world, but less well known elsewhere.

3396
05:05:05,291 --> 05:05:06,052
BBC News.

3397
05:05:09,176 --> 05:05:09,756
Thanks very much.

3398
05:05:09,776 --> 05:05:13,759
You're listening to the Newsroom from the BBC World Service with Oliver Conway.

3399
05:05:14,440 --> 05:05:16,161
In a speech at 1 p.m.

3400
05:05:16,181 --> 05:05:20,504
local time in Washington, Donald Trump is expected to announce that the U.S.

3401
05:05:20,544 --> 05:05:26,748
will recognize Jerusalem as the capital of Israel, upending years of American policy on the Middle East.

3402
05:05:27,348 --> 05:05:32,111
According to briefings from senior White House officials, the president will start the process of moving the U.S.

3403
05:05:32,232 --> 05:05:36,074
embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem, although that could take years.

3404
05:05:36,735 --> 05:05:52,886
The decision to recognize Jerusalem would put America at odds with almost every other nation in the world, and Mr Trump was warned about the possible dire consequences of the move when he spoke to Arab leaders, including the Palestinian president, on Tuesday, as we heard from Yolande Nel in Jerusalem.

3405
05:05:53,749 --> 05:05:59,773
In their phone call, the Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas is said to have warned Mr Trump that moving the U.S.

3406
05:05:59,873 --> 05:06:04,836
Embassy would have an impact on the peace process with Israel and regional stability.

3407
05:06:05,376 --> 05:06:11,920
Mr Abbas has since spoken to the Pope and the leaders of Russia, France and Jordan, asking them to intervene.

3408
05:06:12,560 --> 05:06:19,985
King Abdullah of Jordan was also called by Mr Trump and is said to have spoken of possible dangerous repercussions of his plan.

3409
05:06:20,765 --> 05:06:26,639
Egypt's President Sisi is reported to have told him there was no need to complicate matters in the Middle East.

3410
05:06:27,892 --> 05:06:44,198
Now, the White House official did say that Mr Trump recognized that boundaries of Israeli sovereignty in Jerusalem were subject to final status negotiations between Israel and the Palestinians, and also that he was prepared to support a two-state solution if both sides agree.

3411
05:06:44,738 --> 05:06:47,479
But what is the thinking behind the change in policy?

3412
05:06:47,699 --> 05:06:50,180
I spoke to our correspondent in the U.S., Peter Bowes.

3413
05:06:50,940 --> 05:07:09,419
It was part of his campaign pledge that he wanted to do this and it was one of his major foreign policy planks and perhaps domestic policy comes into this a little bit in terms of the president wanting to be seen to be making good on those big promises in his first year.

3414
05:07:09,479 --> 05:07:12,603
I mentioned domestic politics because it hasn't necessarily all gone his way.

3415
05:07:13,023 --> 05:07:14,464
in terms of those big promises.

3416
05:07:14,524 --> 05:07:20,726
So I think he wants to get something done, and I think he is known as quite an impatient character in this respect.

3417
05:07:20,986 --> 05:07:28,189
But in terms of doing it now, I think there are quite a few people here who are rather mystified by the timing.

3418
05:07:28,349 --> 05:07:32,651
We know that the White House, the Trump administration, has been working on a peace plan for several months.

3419
05:07:32,731 --> 05:07:34,392
We don't know the detail of that.

3420
05:07:34,832 --> 05:07:48,237
So why to make this announcement now, perhaps ahead of a bigger plan and bigger negotiations, I think we remain to see, because it does show the US's hand.

3421
05:07:48,277 --> 05:08:02,042
And if the US is going to play a role as a mediator in negotiations between the Palestinians and the Israelis, it perhaps makes things rather awkward, because it's certainly not what the Palestinians wanted to hear.

3422
05:08:02,602 --> 05:08:03,283
Peter Bowes.

3423
05:08:04,043 --> 05:08:10,088
Russia has reacted angrily after the International Olympic Committee banned its team from the forthcoming Winter Olympics.

3424
05:08:10,529 --> 05:08:19,697
The International Olympic Committee's decision comes after their damning report said that Moscow was guilty of an unprecedented systematic manipulation of the anti-doping system.

3425
05:08:20,177 --> 05:08:27,483
The decision has been welcomed by Dr. Grigory Radchenov, a Russian lab director who was the original whistleblower on the scandal.

3426
05:08:27,904 --> 05:08:29,305
Jim Walden is his lawyer.

3427
05:08:29,945 --> 05:08:35,067
Taking a country as powerful as Russia and saying you can't compete is a very significant penalty.

3428
05:08:35,627 --> 05:08:46,111
It shows that Russia and other countries who break the rules in this kind of a pervasive way need to be held accountable.

3429
05:08:46,891 --> 05:08:51,593
And so from that perspective, I think that it was a step that will help march us toward reform.

3430
05:08:52,061 --> 05:08:57,045
Well, in Russia itself, the Deputy Speaker of Parliament called the ban a humiliation and an insult.

3431
05:08:57,565 --> 05:09:00,447
And President Putin is due to speak about it later today.

3432
05:09:00,888 --> 05:09:03,830
Well, let's get reaction from the country actually hosting the Games.

3433
05:09:03,870 --> 05:09:05,831
Paul Adams is in South Korea.

3434
05:09:06,492 --> 05:09:11,595
I think everyone knew that the IOC was poised to take this unprecedented step.

3435
05:09:12,136 --> 05:09:14,698
And so the reaction here has been pretty measured.

3436
05:09:15,238 --> 05:09:26,260
The head of the committee here, Lee Hee Boom, said that it was the second-best alternative, a reference, obviously, to the fact that Russian athletes deemed to be clean will be able to attend.

3437
05:09:26,741 --> 05:09:27,921
He welcomed that decision.

3438
05:09:28,281 --> 05:09:30,401
There was a statement from the organizing committee.

3439
05:09:30,421 --> 05:09:33,002
We accept and respect the decisions of the IOC.

3440
05:09:33,562 --> 05:09:37,303
And they're very keen to emphasize that these games go ahead regardless.

3441
05:09:37,843 --> 05:09:42,986
The head of the organizing committee said he wasn't particularly worried about the impact on ticket sales.

3442
05:09:43,026 --> 05:09:45,848
He felt that those were going reasonably well.

3443
05:09:46,488 --> 05:09:50,891
Russia is strong in some areas and not so strong in others.

3444
05:09:50,951 --> 05:09:54,333
It's not a big downhill skiing nation, for example.

3445
05:09:54,773 --> 05:09:56,294
But it is a near neighbor.

3446
05:09:56,654 --> 05:10:01,237
The South Koreans must have been expecting significant numbers of Russian fans to show up.

3447
05:10:01,777 --> 05:10:02,958
And that obviously is not going to happen.

3448
05:10:03,398 --> 05:10:05,019
Paul Adams in South Korea.

3449
05:10:05,959 --> 05:10:12,583
Eastern Ghouta, a suburb of the Syrian capital Damascus, has faced unrelenting bombardment over the past three weeks.

3450
05:10:13,163 --> 05:10:16,905
A ceasefire announced recently didn't even hold for a full 24 hours.

3451
05:10:17,606 --> 05:10:23,509
As the death toll from airstrikes continues to rise, so too does the number of children nearing starvation.

3452
05:10:23,829 --> 05:10:30,933
The UN has said that acute malnutrition among youngsters is at the highest level recorded anywhere in Syria since the war began.

3453
05:10:31,673 --> 05:10:34,313
Our correspondent Martin Patience reports from Eastern Ghouta.

3454
05:10:38,314 --> 05:10:43,315
The aftermath of the latest airstrikes is like a scene from hell.

3455
05:10:44,035 --> 05:10:50,296
The sky is dark with dust and debris as rescuers rush into buildings to scoop up children.

3456
05:10:51,436 --> 05:10:54,657
Among the injured was five-year-old Yusuf with a head wound.

3457
05:10:55,397 --> 05:11:01,058
The doctors patch him up as best they can, but they're desperately short of medical supplies.

